1.m_mPlotText: "Ami, I found a sketchbook in the kitchen the other day. It had meat stains on it. Was it yours?"

2.m_mPlotText: "It's not mine. And please don't go imagining me sneaking into the kitchen, stealing food, and dropping things."

3.m_mPlotText: "I see... I was going to say—the drawings in it were really good."

4.m_mPlotText: "Well then, if the drawings were really good... It must be mine after all."

5.m_mPlotText: "Your sketches of the El Dorado helped us uncover the ship's mysteries before. I didn't realize you'd drawn so many... interesting stories as well."

6.m_mPlotText: "When I was little, I'd often watch the Captain and William scribbling on paper."

7.m_mPlotText: "One wrote navigation logs while the other kept lab notes. I wanted to write a diary too, but I didn't know how to read and write then... so I started drawing instead."

8.m_mPlotText: "So that sketch on the first page, with the childing handwriting and the "Captain Demon" title... was that your earliest work?"

9.m_mPlotText: "I must've thought the Captain was terrifying back then. Like some moody "demon.""

10.m_mPlotText: "Because his attitude toward you would suddenly turn cold... then warm again?"

11.m_mPlotText: "Exactly. Sometimes he'd be so thoughtful, and other times... distant, like a stranger."

12.m_mPlotText: "Still, I'd say most of the time, he's just the same arrogant, self-absorbed Captain we all knew."

13.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Sometimes I wonder, Ami—do you ever miss life aboard the El Dorado?"

2.m_mPlotText: "Have you been looking at my drawings again? When are you planning to return them?"

3.m_mPlotText: "I just wanted to ask—when you drew that bird in a cage, was it because you felt trapped on the El Dorado?"

4.m_mPlotText: "I used to watch the seabirds fly freely above the water. I tried to escape the ship to be like them."

5.m_mPlotText: "But the crew always caught me and brought me back."

6.m_mPlotText: "They must have been worried about you."

7.m_mPlotText: "Sounds like you just weren't fast enough."

8.m_mPlotText: "Captain and the others always said: "Land is dangerous.""

9.m_mPlotText: "I heard you were burned alive. Guess you couldn't outrun the Inquisitor either, huh?"

10.m_mPlotText: "The travelers who came aboard always told me stories about life on land—and all the delicious food there. But I never understood why everyone else on the ship kept saying the land was dangerous."

11.m_mPlotText: "Yet every time they came back from shore, they looked so happy. Smiling, laughing… sailing off to the next port..."

12.m_mPlotText: "Adventure always carries both joy and danger."

13.m_mPlotText: "There are some things children aren't allowed to do."

14.m_mPlotText: "You sound just like First Mate Bob. Is that how all older people talk?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Second Mate Aaron said the same thing. Honestly, it sounds more like a villain's excuse than a grown-up's well-meaning lie."

16.m_mPlotText: "Sounds like you're already starting to miss the people and the life you had on that ship."

17.m_mPlotText: "No further replies came—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "So, Ami—you wanted to be a cook and a sailor?"

2.m_mPlotText: "I take it you're never giving my sketchbook back."

3.m_mPlotText: "What made you interested in those two jobs?"

4.m_mPlotText: "I thought being a cook meant I could eat whatever I wanted. But that just got me kicked out."

5.m_mPlotText: "Then I thought being a sailor meant having fun every day. It was fun… but I kept catching colds."

6.m_mPlotText: "So why did you end up becoming a maid?"

7.m_mPlotText: "Why not consider becoming an artist?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Because the Captain said, "you should do work that isn't dangerous.""

9.m_mPlotText: "Because of people like you—who find my sketchbook and never give it back."

10.m_mPlotText: "So Goldland really was protecting you, after all."

11.m_mPlotText: "But when I don't clean properly, he scolds me too… That cold side of him still shows up at times."

12.m_mPlotText: "Speaking of which—it looks like the last page of the sketchbook was torn out. What was drawn there?"

13.m_mPlotText: "With your curiosity, I doubt you'll return the sketchbook until you've seen every page."

14.m_mPlotText: "Maybe next time. I’ll tell you when the time comes."

15.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Some time passed after last exchange, before another letter from Ami finally arrived."

2.m_mPlotText: "Remember when you mentioned there was a page missing from the sketchbook?"

3.m_mPlotText: "Are you finally going to tell me what was on it?"

4.m_mPlotText: "You were so secretive back then... but now I’m not even sure I want to know."

5.m_mPlotText: "Actually, that missing page was left behind on the El Dorado. I was hoping you could help me find it."

6.m_mPlotText: "So you didn't tear it out yourself?"

7.m_mPlotText: "But hasn’t that ship already sunk?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Why would I tear out one of my own drawings?"

9.m_mPlotText: "That's part of the main story. We're in the Affinity story now—so it's still around."

10.m_mPlotText: "Then maybe you could start by telling me what the drawing was?"

11.m_mPlotText: "No further replies came—for now."

12.m_mPlotText: "Keeping silent? I suppose I’ll see for myself once I find it."

13.m_mPlotText: "By the coast, Ami's lost sketchbook was reclaimed from a mutated enemy."

14.m_mPlotText: "(So the missing page showed everyone gathered aboard the El Dorado.)"

15.m_mPlotText: "(Goldland, Bob, Aaron, William… and all the sailors.)"

16.m_mPlotText: "(Now that I think about it, that mutated enemy was clutching this drawing… Even in death, they wouldn't let it go.)"

17.m_mPlotText: "(Better not tell Ami about this.)"

18.m_mPlotText: "Ami, I found your missing drawing. Shall we meet at the castle? I’ll return the sketchbook—complete this time."

19.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "It's time to deliver the final drawing to Ami."
"To my most cherished customer:"

2.m_mPlotText: "It's that thrilling time again—monthly collection! This month's balance: 5,000,000,000 Soli. Please settle your account at your earliest convenience."

3.m_mPlotText: "Are you sure you have the right person?"

4.m_mPlotText: "(Read and no reply.)"

5.m_mPlotText: "The Puppet Association is famed for its accounting to the last Soli. We do not err in calculations—nor in identifying debtors."

6.m_mPlotText: "I think the phrase you're looking for is accurate to the last Soli."

7.m_mPlotText: "Your full name is Noah Nevernight, is it not? The Puppet Association maintains detailed records of all outstanding accounts."

8.m_mPlotText: "Wait a minute."

9.m_mPlotText: "Elder Bella? I apologize, but I don't recall spending that much."

10.m_mPlotText: "I am Yakov, Elder Bella's most trusted puppet."

11.m_mPlotText: "Allow me to check the invoice... Ah—here it is. The largest expense:"

12.m_mPlotText: "Activation fee for the Power Furnace."

13.m_mPlotText: "This doesn't seem to be my expense."

14.m_mPlotText: "Then someone must've activated it on your behalf."

15.m_mPlotText: "Ingratitude does not suit a Lord. I suggest you find a way to repay your debt—promptly."

16.m_mPlotText: "I don't have that kind of Soli."

17.m_mPlotText: "Is that so? Well, since you're a valued customer, Yakov is pleased to offer a special repayment option:"

18.m_mPlotText: "Assist the Puppet Association in collecting other debts to settle your own."

19.m_mPlotText: "First stop: Verse & Valor. Please depart at once. We do not wait."

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

21.m_mPlotText: "(Looks like I have no choice but to start collecting these debts.)"

1.m_mPlotText: "I didn't expect the first collection to go so smoothly. I should report back to Yakov."

2.m_mPlotText: "Payment from Verse & Valor has been collected. Please check."

3.m_mPlotText: "Brilliant, absolutely brilliant! As expected of a client personally selected by Elder Bella."

4.m_mPlotText: "Did you pay our dear Mr. Derek a visit on behalf of the Puppet Association?"

5.m_mPlotText: "I didn't expect you to show such concern for your clients."

6.m_mPlotText: "He did mention your prices are rather high."

7.m_mPlotText: "Those who enter our doors are honored guests; those who make payment become dear friends."

8.m_mPlotText: "To serve all with utmost enthusiasm—this is Yakov's ironclad principle."

9.m_mPlotText: "Could Mr. Derek be mistaken?"

10.m_mPlotText: "The Puppet Association only ever picks the juiciest—Ahem, I mean our prices haven't changed in the slightest!"

11.m_mPlotText: "Well then, enough small talk. The next stop should be—"

12.m_mPlotText: "Wait."

13.m_mPlotText: "Mr. Derek mentioned Elder Bella's been reading a lot of philosophy lately. Books about "the self," and the nature of existence."

14.m_mPlotText: "Is she doing well?"

15.m_mPlotText: "My, my, showing concern for Lady Bella, are we?"

16.m_mPlotText: "Only natural. Too much contemplation of the self can lead to a spiral of nihilism. That's all."

17.m_mPlotText: "Such thoughtful insight, from our silver-haired friend!"

18.m_mPlotText: "Lady Bella's been spending all her time locked away in the study. That's why the debts have piled up."

19.m_mPlotText: "I understand. I'll continue doing what I can."

20.m_mPlotText: "Such efficiency! In that case—let's add one more collection to your list for today."

21.m_mPlotText: "Let's see… ah! Next client: Cain the steward."

22.m_mPlotText: "The sooner we recover the funds, the sooner we can fulfill Lady Bella's wishes. Ah, Yakov truly is a genius!"

23.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "(Cain's payment still hasn't been resolved… and now we know Bella is looking into Bell Ringer Joyce.)"

2.m_mPlotText: "(This may be more serious than I thought. I should write to Elder Bella directly to confirm.)"

3.m_mPlotText: "Elder Bella, apologies for the interruption."

4.m_mPlotText: "Cain has proposed settling this month's payment with information."

5.m_mPlotText: "Just Bella is fine. I'm not nearly old enough to need formal titles."

6.m_mPlotText: "Did Cain say anything else?"

7.m_mPlotText: "He says you're investigating Joyce."

8.m_mPlotText: "He says you're seeking to do business with the Bell Ringers."

9.m_mPlotText: "Oh dear… how quickly my little secret was uncovered."

10.m_mPlotText: "But high risk brings high reward. This might turn out to be quite the lucrative venture."

11.m_mPlotText: "Tell me—do you know Joyce?"

12.m_mPlotText: "I've heard of him. The Bell Ringer who pioneered the Church's mechanical Ascendant project… A Puppet with certain peculiar traits."

13.m_mPlotText: "And do you see me as a peculiar puppet too?"

14.m_mPlotText: "Not at all."

15.m_mPlotText: "Puppet, maiden, merchant, Elder—these are merely labels the world imposes."

16.m_mPlotText: "To me, Bella is simply Bella. Unbound by names. Undefined by roles."

17.m_mPlotText: "What an intriguing answer."

18.m_mPlotText: "So, would you say Bella counts as a living, breathing person—the kind Baphomet is so fond of?"

19.m_mPlotText: "Is that why you've locked yourself away in the study? To decide whether you're truly a Puppet… or something more?"

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

21.m_mPlotText: "Elder Bella has left her seat, but the collections must continue!"

22.m_mPlotText: "Next client... Well, give him an easy one."

23.m_mPlotText: "Go find Miss Dalcarlo."

1.m_mPlotText: "Our silver-haired friend certainly enjoys meddling. Helping with collections is one thing, but now you're involving yourself in Dalcarlo's affairs too?"

2.m_mPlotText: "I was just about to write you when your letter arrived."

3.m_mPlotText: "This is my business. And your constant interference is making it quite difficult."

4.m_mPlotText: "Is there a misunderstanding?"

5.m_mPlotText: "Yakov told me to collect debts—to repay my debt."

6.m_mPlotText: "First, the Puppet Association is not short-staffed."

7.m_mPlotText: "Second, you owe us nothing."

8.m_mPlotText: "How curious... What is Yakov's real reason for drawing you into Association matters?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Not only that, but deliberately letting me discover your secrets."

10.m_mPlotText: "Your philosophical studies... your investigation into Joyce... Your arrangement with Dalcarlo in Sapphire Isle..."

11.m_mPlotText: "I understand now."

12.m_mPlotText: "Yakov wanted to help me fulfill my "wish.""

13.m_mPlotText: "Your next task is to restock our supplies in Sapphire Isle."

14.m_mPlotText: "Wait. What are you really trying to do?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Yakov is trying to help me find myself. I'm not sure if that's possible."

16.m_mPlotText: "So the real reason for going to Sapphire Isle… Could it be that it's your hometown?"

17.m_mPlotText: "That depends on how you define "hometown.""

18.m_mPlotText: "A hometown is where the ones you care for still remain."

19.m_mPlotText: "A hometown is where everything begins."

20.m_mPlotText: "Then Sapphire Isle doesn't count. The Black Blood disease turned it into a dead city long ago."

21.m_mPlotText: "No one remains. Nothing remains."

22.m_mPlotText: "In a sense, Sapphire Isle is my hometown."

23.m_mPlotText: "Everything about me began there."

24.m_mPlotText: "Once you've finished collecting the local specialties from Sapphire Isle, come to my room."

25.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "When delivering Sapphire Isle's specialty to Elder Bella's room, I unexpectedly uncovered a surprising truth."
"Cain, there was a loud noise in the castle just now. It seemed to come from your room. Did something happen?"

2.m_mPlotText: "Heh, good guess."

3.m_mPlotText: "Should I say this is just like you? Always causing "explosive" incidents."

4.m_mPlotText: "Don't forget to pay the Soli for the repairs."

5.m_mPlotText: "Thanks for the compliment."

6.m_mPlotText: "Do we really need to worry about such things between us?"

7.m_mPlotText: "I need a favor from you. I'm sure our "hero" Noah won't refuse me, right?"

8.m_mPlotText: "No, I refuse."

9.m_mPlotText: "What's the favor?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Don't be so quick to refuse. The reward will certainly satisfy you."

11.m_mPlotText: "My experiment has hit a bottleneck. The book says "Add two parts moonlight's radiance, one part golden seed, and let purity take it all away...""

12.m_mPlotText: "I thought purity meant pure water, but the experimental results seem to differ from my understanding."

13.m_mPlotText: "You're not suggesting I should go get some "truly pure" water, are you?"

14.m_mPlotText: "Good guess. I bet the holy water used in baptisms is the truly pure water we need."

15.m_mPlotText: "As compensation, I'll share the results with you once my experiment succeeds."

16.m_mPlotText: "I need to give this some serious thought."

17.m_mPlotText: "Thanks in advance."

18.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Can you understand my Alchemy Handbook?"

2.m_mPlotText: "How did you know..."

3.m_mPlotText: "But there was only me in the room."

4.m_mPlotText: "For such an esteemed guest, I shall provide nothing less than the most attentive care."

5.m_mPlotText: "But why are you interested in Alchemy? Or perhaps... in me?"

6.m_mPlotText: "Neither."

7.m_mPlotText: "I'm more interested in gold."

8.m_mPlotText: "My advice is to be honest with yourself."

9.m_mPlotText: "So even as a Bloodborn, you cannot escape humanity's mundane desires."

10.m_mPlotText: "I'm just curious—can you really use Alchemy to turn ordinary metals into gold?"

11.m_mPlotText: "If you want to find out, bring me some holy water and see my experimental results."

12.m_mPlotText: "So holy water is the "first material" mentioned in your notes?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Surprising that you could understand my notes."

14.m_mPlotText: "In your eyes, everyone except yourself is stupid, right?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Not necessarily. In my eyes, you're someone quite special."

16.m_mPlotText: "Coming back to that—the "first material" refers to something "most precious yet most cheap, omnipresent yet hardest to find." It should be holy water indeed."

17.m_mPlotText: "Indeed, just as I thought."

18.m_mPlotText: "Then I'll leave this to you, Noah. Go to the Church and bring back some holy water."

19.m_mPlotText: "...Fine."

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I've received the holy water you found. That was quick."

2.m_mPlotText: "...No need to thank me, though you haven't said it yet."

3.m_mPlotText: "That church where I got the holy water—you still have followers there, even though you were merely "God's" messenger back then."

4.m_mPlotText: "Yet it seems their faith in you exceeds their faith in god himself."

5.m_mPlotText: "Why do you think humans believe in god?"

6.m_mPlotText: "Because humans have limited understanding of the world, so they try to explain the incomprehensible through faith?"

7.m_mPlotText: "That's one perspective. In truth, when the first spark illuminated the earth, humanity forever lost its blissful ignorance."

8.m_mPlotText: "Thus, to escape the burden of thinking and the responsibility it brings, humans created gods to bear the weight of their thoughts."

9.m_mPlotText: "I merely did what their "god" did—I made divine proclamations on their behalf, relieving them of thought and guilt. Naturally, they followed me."

10.m_mPlotText: "Therefore, god is not an inherent existence, but a human creation."

11.m_mPlotText: "So you believe humans are foolish and gods are powerless?"

12.m_mPlotText: "But I believe humans simply have too many uncertainties about the world."

13.m_mPlotText: "Indeed."

14.m_mPlotText: "Humans need the existence of an omnipotent "God" to maintain coherence in their understanding of the world."

15.m_mPlotText: "Interesting perspective, worth pondering..."

16.m_mPlotText: "Corresponding with you has sparked a rare interest in me, but I must attend to my experiments now. Let's continue this discussion another time."

17.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "One last favor I'd like to ask—could you find something for me?"

2.m_mPlotText: "With it, my experiments would have a much higher chance of success."

3.m_mPlotText: "What is it?"

4.m_mPlotText: "I can't tell you yet, but the item is in the Hall of Opulence at Bathory Castle. It's a slender bottle containing a small amount of red liquid."

5.m_mPlotText: "...Stealing holy water wasn't enough, now you want me to steal from the Bathory family treasury?"

6.m_mPlotText: "Ah, sacrificing yourself for the pursuit of truth, are you?"

7.m_mPlotText: "Among the glittering treasures in the Hall of Opulence, that bottle of wine sits rather unremarkably."

8.m_mPlotText: "There, I've got what you wanted."

9.m_mPlotText: "This wouldn't happen to be the last remaining blood of the Matriarch? The security was incredibly tight. I had to knock out quite a few guards to get it."

10.m_mPlotText: "If you want to know more, bring it to me. Perfect timing—my experiments are reaching their final stage."

11.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I found the treasure for Cain. It's time to deliver it to him."

"To my dear <s>silver-haired heretic</s>, if by fortune's grace you yet live: An old friend claims to have seen someone with your face, wandering the Lupine Forest. If you are indeed still breathing, I would be both <s>surprised</s> and genuinely pleased to hear from you."

2.m_mPlotText: "You've already found where I live. Why bother pretending you haven't?"

3.m_mPlotText: "A man like you... has friends?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Because I truly do hope the rumors are true, that you, my friend, are still alive."

5.m_mPlotText: "So that's what troubles you. How cruel of you... But you know, my silver-haired friend, I've always thought of you as one of my own."

6.m_mPlotText: "Burning someone the first time you meet them doesn't exactly qualify as friendship."

7.m_mPlotText: "And aside from that day, we've had no further contact. I don't consider strangers to be friends."

8.m_mPlotText: "Still as cold as ever. If you're blaming me for my 'work,' I won't make excuses. But if the problem is that we've never truly understood each other..."

9.m_mPlotText: "Then why not start now? Let this letter be my chance to properly introduce myself."

10.m_mPlotText: "Is this how you treat your "friends"? Because you were "born from a corpse"?"

11.m_mPlotText: "And your ruthlessness as an inquisitor... Does that come from having "two hearts"?"

12.m_mPlotText: "No one remembers their own birth, do they? Even I only heard that story through rumors. Who knows if it's true?"

13.m_mPlotText: "I'll admit I'm not quite like ordinary men. As for whether I truly have two hearts... well, maybe you'll have to come hear for yourself."

14.m_mPlotText: "That said, where exactly did you come across these tales? They're even numbered like some twisted nursery rhyme. There must be more. What else have they been saying about me?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Each one costs a drink. We'll continue next time. If we meet again."

16.m_mPlotText: "No reply came. Perhaps he had gone to seek out the rest of the tales on his own."

1.m_mPlotText: "To my silver-haired friend, who may have been swayed by those rumors about me: I was planning to spend a quiet holiday at Ellington Bay, but this matter keeps nagging at me. Why not just tell me who's been spreading them?"

2.m_mPlotText: "I thought you wouldn't care."

3.m_mPlotText: "What choice do I have? My Knights barely listen to me as it is, and now they're hearing I devoured my own siblings. The way they look at me grows more suspicious by the day."

4.m_mPlotText: "That's what happens when your authority was never solid to begin with."

5.m_mPlotText: "Were they tasty?"

6.m_mPlotText: "Well, I do take pride in being the second most idle Bell Ringer. As the saying goes: the less you give, the less you get, but you gain plenty of rest."

7.m_mPlotText: "That's why the whole thing is absurd. I don't even eat meat."

8.m_mPlotText: "No smoke without fire. Whether it's the "three siblings" or the "four names," they must've existed in your life in some form."

9.m_mPlotText: "Do you always speak so bluntly when prodding at another's wounds?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Is this how all inquisitors dodge questions?"

11.m_mPlotText: "I know."

12.m_mPlotText: "My friend, you really do have a sharp tongue."

13.m_mPlotText: "My past burns hotter than flame. You'd do well to tread carefully."

14.m_mPlotText: "Come to think of it, perhaps it's no surprise. I've lived through four identities, and the last is to become the Bell Ringer that the world now knows. No wonder people talk."

15.m_mPlotText: "Four identities. Four names. That explains where the rumors began."

16.m_mPlotText: "A manor slave. Chancellor of Carrelle. The Church's Bell Ringer. And... my personal favorite, "The Poet of Flame." That makes four, doesn't it?"

17.m_mPlotText: "You were once a slave and a chancellor? Two roles that couldn't be more opposed. It's hard to believe either of them led to the man you are now."

18.m_mPlotText: "Ah, the stories behind those two... Well, this letter would run far too long if I started telling them here."

19.m_mPlotText: "Then what about the three siblings? What do they represent?"

20.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps I had different family in each of those lives... Who knows?"

21.m_mPlotText: "No replies for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "To my silver-haired friend, always eager to catch my attention: You interrupted me last time. So, will you finally tell me who's been wandering around spreading my "tales"?"

2.m_mPlotText: "Unfortunately, he always finds me. I never know where he'll turn up next."

3.m_mPlotText: "Now, now, based on what I've heard, you don't just know him. You might be very familiar with him."

4.m_mPlotText: "What exactly are you implying?"

5.m_mPlotText: "Several soldiers who heard those tales described this... "storyteller" as a person dressed in black, with silver hair, red eyes... and fangs."

6.m_mPlotText: "You're not seriously suggesting it's me."

7.m_mPlotText: "Sounds like a rather handsome man."

8.m_mPlotText: "Those were your words, not mine. We've only met once, after all. I can't say I remember your face that clearly."

9.m_mPlotText: "I never mentioned their gender. Seems you gave yourself away."

10.m_mPlotText: "I've no idea why anyone would think that's me, but let me make one thing clear. I didn't know you before, nor did I have any interest in doing so."

11.m_mPlotText: "Of course I know you're not that kind of person. If I had to guess... someone went out of their way to take your form."

12.m_mPlotText: "That old man? I thought there was something strange about him from the start. But why would he do this?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Ah... so the "storyteller"you met appeared as an old man? So they can alter not only their appearance, but even their age. Who could they be?"

14.m_mPlotText: "I think I'm starting to understand how it feels to be dragged into these "rumors." If I see him again, I'll be more careful."

15.m_mPlotText: "I'll await your news."

16.m_mPlotText: "No replies for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "To my silver-haired friend, always so reluctant to share anything useful: I've tracked down that individual's whereabouts. Leave the rest to me. You should get some rest."

2.m_mPlotText: "Who is this person that can take on my form?"

3.m_mPlotText: "So you've finally realized it was me?"

4.m_mPlotText: "A being that no longer belongs to our world."

5.m_mPlotText: "You do have a sense of humor. Even if you've become one of the Bloodborn, you're still very much alive, aren't you?"

6.m_mPlotText: "From the sound of it, they're not among the living."

7.m_mPlotText: "You're not far off. To be precise, they are the ghosts that have haunted me for a long time."

8.m_mPlotText: "I thought, after all these years, they might have laid their hatred to rest. I didn't expect them to return like this."

9.m_mPlotText: "Ghosts? I wouldn't have expected a Grand Inquisitor of the Church to believe in such things."

10.m_mPlotText: "There are too many phenomena in this world, things that not even a Saint or the divine, can explain."

11.m_mPlotText: "Take this for example: Why can "they" shift their appearance at will? Those fanatical scholars in the Church would stop at nothing to obtain that kind of power."

12.m_mPlotText: "What I find more curious is... Why would a ghost so obsessed with you choose to take on my form in front of others?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps you, I, and they... all died the same death. Consumed by flames."

14.m_mPlotText: "If I’m understanding this correctly… You, a Grand Inquisitor who has sentenced countless heretics to the fire, have experienced something similar yourself?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Ghosts are drawn to places and people who share their feelings. It's no different from the Black Blood disease and the beasts it spawns. You of all people should know that."

16.m_mPlotText: "That doesn't answer my question. You've only explained what we share in common. But I still don't know why they resent you. Or why I've been dragged into this."

17.m_mPlotText: "Let's leave it at that. Since we finally have a lead on the source of these rumors, I don't have much time to waste."

18.m_mPlotText: "No replies for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Some time passed after their last exchange before Agares sent another letter."

2.m_mPlotText: "How have you been, my silver-haired friend? Forgive the delay, I've been quite occupied with work."

3.m_mPlotText: "No need for formalities. If you're asking about that shape-shifting '$ghost,' I haven't seen them in some time. What surprises me more is that you still haven't caught them."

4.m_mPlotText: "As sharp as ever. While this isn't entirely unrelated to "them," I'm reaching out for another reason. There's a matter I can't attend to personally, and I was hoping you might lend a hand."

5.m_mPlotText: "A Bell Ringer asking for help from a "heretic"?"

6.m_mPlotText: "I decline."

7.m_mPlotText: "If I were to intervene myself, things might escalate beyond control. Besides, if you agree, I can ensure the Inquisition won't trouble you for some time."

8.m_mPlotText: "Come now, no need to be so cold. Agree to help, and I'll make sure the Inquisition keeps their distance."

9.m_mPlotText: "There's a small manor in eastern Carrelle territory that's been suffering repeated raids by bandits. I'd like you to drive them off and help the people there."

10.m_mPlotText: "Shouldn't that fall to the Church? They're the ones sworn to protect them."

11.m_mPlotText: "Any case, I'll leave it in your hands. Your reward will be ready when you return."

12.m_mPlotText: "But I never agreed to help you."

13.m_mPlotText: "No reply has come since."

14.m_mPlotText: "He's a man who keeps his promises, and the reward isn't bad. Besides, there might be answers there. Something that sheds light on the truth behind the rumors."

15.m_mPlotText: "Eastern Carrelle isn't far. I may as well take a look."

16.m_mPlotText: "The thugs were much easier to deal with than Agares. I quickly eliminated them all."

17.m_mPlotText: "But this manor is even more remote than I expected, and there aren't many people living here. Why would someone like Agares care so much about a place like this..."

18.m_mPlotText: "Wait... all the villages share the surname "Brennholt"—same as Agares. Could this be... his hometown?"

19.m_mPlotText: "I should pay him a visit. He still owes me a reward, after all."

20.m_mPlotText: "No replies for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I'll collect my rightful reward, but more importantly, there are crucial matters I need to confirm with him."
"I'm giving you three days. Return to the castle within that time."

2.m_mPlotText: "Lamia? I can't return right now. What's the matter?"

3.m_mPlotText: "Still hanging around that boring one? I really don't understand why you all flock to her."

4.m_mPlotText: "Since you won't return, you shall help me solve Cain's puzzle instead."

5.m_mPlotText: "I hate to admit it, but I still haven't solved the puzzle he gave me."

6.m_mPlotText: "What if I refuse?"

7.m_mPlotText: "We'll start with mine."

8.m_mPlotText: "As a Bathory Vassal, you have no right to refuse me."

9.m_mPlotText: "However, Cain only poses clues to those who desire something. I wonder, what is it you seek?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Me? Seeking from him? Never!"

11.m_mPlotText: "He's the one who trapped us in this castle, and I'm sick of his little game. Now he dares to put obstacles in my way when I want to leave... He's asking for trouble!"

12.m_mPlotText: "You want to leave the castle?"

13.m_mPlotText: "That fool, No. 66, said before she died that if I ever got tired of this game, I should look for the great tree by the cliff at Howling Heights."

14.m_mPlotText: "She buried a weapon beneath that tree, one powerful enough to end all of this."

15.m_mPlotText: "That's why I must get out. Once I'm free, I'll claim the power No. 66 left behind and eliminate all of you who stand in my way."

16.m_mPlotText: "But Cain had to meddle, saying I can only leave if I solve his stupid puzzle."

17.m_mPlotText: "The question is—I must prove that whatever my "sisters" can do, I can do as well."

18.m_mPlotText: "But damn it, what haven't I accomplished yet?!"

19.m_mPlotText: "I understand. If it's for the sake of freedom, I'll help you."

20.m_mPlotText: "Ha! If you want to dress up this deal as something noble, be my guest."

21.m_mPlotText: "First, we need to identify your previous shortcomings, or rather, what you've failed to achieve. Shall we start by examining your shared experiences?"

22.m_mPlotText: "The Moonfall Games—that's where I first met my so-called "sisters.""

23.m_mPlotText: "Let's start here and end this ridiculous game."

24.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "(It's been a while since I received a letter from Lamia. I wonder if she's solved the puzzle.)"

2.m_mPlotText: "(I heard she's been spending day and night at the arena. Perhaps I should write to ask how she's doing.)"

3.m_mPlotText: "I hear you've made the arena your home lately. It seems you've found a way to solve the puzzle."

4.m_mPlotText: "I have some discoveries to share with you as well."

5.m_mPlotText: "Too slow."

6.m_mPlotText: "If this were the Moonfall Games, you'd be dead already with that information gathering speed."

7.m_mPlotText: "I've reviewed the records about the Moonfall Games."

8.m_mPlotText: "I don't see any aspect of your performance that falls short of others."

9.m_mPlotText: "In fact, according to the records, your scores from the Hall of the Elders rank among the highest in all categories."

10.m_mPlotText: "You've got brains—no wonder Empousa took an interest in you."

11.m_mPlotText: "Yes, I also thought Cain wanted me to prove I possess strength equal to my "sisters.""

12.m_mPlotText: "That's why I've been training relentlessly in the arena, until no opponent could match me anymore."

13.m_mPlotText: "I brought the arena medal to Cain, but alas, I was wrong... even if that medal was supposed to be the symbol of our family's ultimate strength."

14.m_mPlotText: "That old fox said that where I fall short of them isn't about strength."

15.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps it's not about obvious measures like strength, but something deeper?"

16.m_mPlotText: "For instance... ideals?"

17.m_mPlotText: "Are you mocking my lack of ideals?"

18.m_mPlotText: "That's not what I meant."

20.m_mPlotText: "You're right. Compared to No. 66 with her head full of stars and seas, I truly have no ideals."

21.m_mPlotText: "Who would have thought, after all these years, we'd face off again like this—I'm looking forward to it, No. 66."

22.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "(It's been a while since I received a letter from Lamia. I wonder if she's made any progress with the puzzle.)"

2.m_mPlotText: "(I heard she's been spending all her time in the archives lately. Perhaps I should write her a letter.)"

3.m_mPlotText: "How's the puzzle-solving going?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Tell me, what are ideals truly about?"

5.m_mPlotText: "It's "returning home.""

6.m_mPlotText: "It means to hold onto hope, no matter what."

7.m_mPlotText: "I can't believe how naive you are. That's nothing but this family's most foolish delusion."

8.m_mPlotText: "Clinging to hope when you know there's no escape isn't an ideal—it's pure foolishness."

9.m_mPlotText: "Is this why you spend all your time in the archives—searching for answers about ideals?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Tell me, Silver-haired, are you watching my every move? Do you have eyes in every corner of the castle, from the arena to the archives?"

11.m_mPlotText: "What I mean is—perhaps Cain's anticipated confrontation has nothing to do with ideals."

12.m_mPlotText: "In truth, neither you nor No. 66 has abandoned hope—you've simply chosen different paths."

13.m_mPlotText: "You're always a step behind... I've been working on this for ages, and you're only now telling me all this."

14.m_mPlotText: "But it wasn't all for nothing, was it?"

15.m_mPlotText: "No. 66 told me she'd definitely visit the archives when she got out."

16.m_mPlotText: "Because the archives contain records of the "returning home" ideal—its origins, evolution, and countless attempts by our predecessors."

17.m_mPlotText: "A paradise free from death, a sanctuary for souls, a perfect utopia... it's so beautiful I'm almost convinced."

18.m_mPlotText: "I read every relevant text with utmost devotion. I thought Cain would let me pass, but alas, my answer was still wrong."

19.m_mPlotText: "Since this path leads nowhere, let's plan our next direction of investigation."

20.m_mPlotText: "Sometimes I think you and that fool No. 66 are quite alike."

21.m_mPlotText: "No further replies came—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "(It's been a long time since the last letter. I wonder if Lamia has given up on solving that puzzle.)"

2.m_mPlotText: "Are you thinking that Lamia has given up?"

3.m_mPlotText: "How did you know?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Don't give up."

5.m_mPlotText: "So you do care about me."

6.m_mPlotText: "Why are you so invested in my affairs?"

7.m_mPlotText: "I hope you can achieve your true wish."

8.m_mPlotText: "What if my true wish is to obtain No. 66's weapons and eliminate all of you?"

9.m_mPlotText: "That can't be your true wish."

10.m_mPlotText: "Don't pretend to understand me."

11.m_mPlotText: "Let me tell you something—I gave up on Cain's puzzle long ago. I'm sick of these mind games."

12.m_mPlotText: "Sorry, I couldn't find the answer for you."

13.m_mPlotText: "If you're truly sorry, go to the market and buy me some jewelry."

14.m_mPlotText: "Send them to me, and I won't bother you anymore."

15.m_mPlotText: "Found the trinket Lamia wanted at the market. It seems to be a favored token exchanged between lovers."

16.m_mPlotText: "I've sent the jewelry with this letter. Though they look like couples' anniversary pieces—what do you want with those?"

17.m_mPlotText: "Got them! Haha, at last this foolish game can come to an end."

18.m_mPlotText: "Are you using the jewelry I bought to solve Cain's puzzle?"

19.m_mPlotText: "Don't be angry. If we're talking about breaking rules, that's Empousa's specialty."

20.m_mPlotText: "You probably don't know yet, do you? She never got approval from the Hall of the Elders to find you in Starfall Valley—she ran away on her own."

21.m_mPlotText: "I don't understand, what do you think Cain wants to test between you two?"

22.m_mPlotText: "After ruling out strength and ideals, there's only one thing I failed to achieve—obtaining you."

23.m_mPlotText: "These letters we've exchanged and these pieces of jewelry should be sufficient proof that I've "obtained you," shouldn't they?"

24.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "The girl is nowhere to be found in the castle. I guess she must have solved the clue and left."
"The Lupine Forest remained as peaceful as ever, even as everyone packed their belongings and prepared to set out."

2.m_mPlotText: "I'm sorry, Noah. I know you're all ready to go, but I'd like to stay in the Lupine Forest a little longer."

3.m_mPlotText: "We thought you might be reminiscing when we couldn't find you."

4.m_mPlotText: "The Lupine Forest to the north is where Clive and I loved to run."

5.m_mPlotText: "That was also where father and Uncle Gadric would practice their combat skill together."

6.m_mPlotText: "Sounds like a place filled with memories."

7.m_mPlotText: "In these past few days, everything, including my home, has ceased to exist."

8.m_mPlotText: "That place must be in ruins now, and those Wolfsbane Clive planted for you..."

9.m_mPlotText: "I'll miss the town, everyone I know here, and those who are no longer with us."

10.m_mPlotText: "They'll live on in your memories."

11.m_mPlotText: "I understand how you feel."

12.m_mPlotText: "As long as they remain in your thoughts, they won't be gone."

13.m_mPlotText: "Uncle Gadric once said something similar. 'The dead will always live on in the memories of the living.'"

14.m_mPlotText: "Though Clive and I haven't known each other for long, our bond runs deeper than you might imagine."

15.m_mPlotText: "And one thing is certain: they would want you to live a happy life."

16.m_mPlotText: "Thank you, Noah. Please wait for me a little longer."

17.m_mPlotText: "I want to run through the forest one last time, just like before."

18.m_mPlotText: "Even though I can't call it home anymore..."

19.m_mPlotText: "We'll wait for you."

20.m_mPlotText: "Come back soon. We'd be lost without your guide."

21.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "As I was about to sleep, faint singing drifted through the window from outside."

2.m_mPlotText: "Hati, is that you?"

3.m_mPlotText: "I never expected a little wolf to sing like that."

4.m_mPlotText: "Forgive me. Did I wake you up?"

5.m_mPlotText: "No worries, I just heard singing coming from Empousa's room, but it didn't sound like her voice, so I sent Feuler to ask about it."

6.m_mPlotText: "Your singing sounds a bit sad."

7.m_mPlotText: "I helped Empousa mend a damaged doll today, which reminded me of Clive Jr. But don't worry, I'm fine—we have to keep moving forward after all!"

8.m_mPlotText: "Are you two living together now? Is she bullying you again? You know, it's okay to feel sad. You don't have to act tough."

9.m_mPlotText: "Don't worry about me, I'm fine. I've always known partings would come, so I won't look back."

10.m_mPlotText: "But Noah, do you ever feel homesick?"

11.m_mPlotText: "Sometimes... After all, home usually carries pleasant memories."

12.m_mPlotText: "What is home, really?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Yeah."

14.m_mPlotText: "It's just a jumbled mess in my mind."

15.m_mPlotText: "Besides, as far as I'm concerned, home is wherever I feel at ease."

16.m_mPlotText: "Since we've left our homes behind, why don't we focus on creating a new one here together?"

17.m_mPlotText: "A new home..."

18.m_mPlotText: "Don't worry, I'm here for you. But first, you need to take that step."

19.m_mPlotText: "Thank you, Noah. I'll do my best."

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Dalcarlo has a message for Hati. Go find her."

2.m_mPlotText: "Hati, why did Dalcarlo just ask me to tell you that she received your things and you can move in now?"

3.m_mPlotText: "It's nothing, nothing at all."

4.m_mPlotText: "Really? She even asked me to help read the cards she drew for you, saying, 'New changes are coming.'"

5.m_mPlotText: "Fine, the truth is I asked Miss Dalcarlo if I could live with her because I just can't get along with that smelly bat anymore!"

6.m_mPlotText: "Miss Dalcarlo agreed, asking in exchange that I make a doll for her cat—such a well-behaved little black cat! Then she offered to draw a card for me."

7.m_mPlotText: "Actually... that black cat was Dalcarlo herself."

8.m_mPlotText: "Oh my! Then I probably have done something really inappropriate..."

9.m_mPlotText: "From what you said, was that card a bad one?"

10.m_mPlotText: "It was the Five of Cups, upright. Miss Dalcarlo said, 'This card represents grief and loss.'"

11.m_mPlotText: "Let me see... The Five of Cups, upright, shows a figure gazing down at three spilled cups, with a river ahead and a bridge fading into the distance."

12.m_mPlotText: "Are you sad, Hati?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps we could add another person to this card."

14.m_mPlotText: "I thought I had let go, but maybe I haven't."

15.m_mPlotText: "But if you look closer at the details, the future isn't all sorrow. Though three cups have fallen, two still stand. If you just turn around, you'll see—you haven’t lost everything."

16.m_mPlotText: "But if you look closer at the details, the future isn't all sorrow. Though three cups have fallen, two still stand. If you just turn around, you'll see—you haven’t lost everything."

17.m_mPlotText: "I have you, and everyone."

18.m_mPlotText: "That bridge will always be waiting for you. Cross it when you're ready, over the river of sorrow and into a new life. We'll all be here waiting."

19.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Upon waking, I found a note slipped under the door. It was in Hati's handwriting."

2.m_mPlotText: "Noah, could you help me with something?"

3.m_mPlotText: "It seemed Hati was facing some difficulties."

4.m_mPlotText: "Hati, I got your note. What do you need help with?"

5.m_mPlotText: "Could you help me gather some Wolfsbane? The flower field that father and Clive planted for me was burned down, but there might be some growing elsewhere."

6.m_mPlotText: "Of course."

7.m_mPlotText: "[Task] Help Hati Find Wolfsbane"

8.m_mPlotText: "Hati, I found the Wolfsbane you asked for."

9.m_mPlotText: "Father once told me he hoped I would be like Wolfsbane. At first, I didn't understand what he meant."

10.m_mPlotText: "Clive meant that he wished for you to be like Wolfsbane—always facing the moon, always growing."

11.m_mPlotText: "Yes, it was only later that I understood his hopes for me."

12.m_mPlotText: "Thank you for helping me reconnect with my father. I think it's time I took a step forward and embraced a new life."

13.m_mPlotText: "Let's meet at the castle tonight. I'll give you the Wolfsbane then."

14.m_mPlotText: "It's settled, then."

15.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Found the Wolfsbane from Hati's memories. Time to hurry and deliver it to her."
"In my mailbox, I found a worn, unfamiliar book—apparently once a well-known folktale."

2.m_mPlotText: "The title page bears the name of its owner: Darcias. I suppose I should write to her about it."

3.m_mPlotText: "(This book belongs to Darcias...? How did it end up with me?)"

4.m_mPlotText: "Darcias, your book somehow ended up in my possession."

5.m_mPlotText: "The Wooden One."

6.m_mPlotText: "The Wooden One?"

7.m_mPlotText: "The long nose...?"

8.m_mPlotText: "You don't know about The Wooden One?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Is it a toy?"

10.m_mPlotText: "No."

11.m_mPlotText: "It's the main character from the book. Some versions avoided copyright by calling it the Iron Person or Stone Person—kind of like a certain rust-prone wanderer from that famous yellow-brick story."

12.m_mPlotText: "I'm sorry, I've never heard of any of them."

13.m_mPlotText: "I see. So Noah can't read. How pitiful."

14.m_mPlotText: "I just haven't read this particular story..."

15.m_mPlotText: "Even more pitiful."

16.m_mPlotText: "No further replies from Darcias—for now."

1.m_mPlotText:
"Lord Noah,

I hope this letter finds you in good health.
Please accept my sincerest apologies for any discourtesy during our recent encounter.
If you would be so kind as to overlook my prior conduct, I wish to make a humble request.

Yours faithfully,
Darcias"

2.m_mPlotText: "(These words… They don't sound like Darcias at all.)"

3.m_mPlotText: "Did Anna dictate this?"

4.m_mPlotText: "You know her?"

5.m_mPlotText: "We've crossed paths."

6.m_mPlotText: "She said my writing was as scattered as my speech, so she offered to refine it."

7.m_mPlotText: "Are you still pitiful?"

8.m_mPlotText: "I finished reading."

9.m_mPlotText: "Anna was right about that..."

10.m_mPlotText: "You were looking for me?"

11.m_mPlotText: "I want to regain my emotions."

12.m_mPlotText: "Why?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Pardon the question, but—aren't emotions considered a burden for Ascendants in battle?"

14.m_mPlotText: "I need a reason to fight."

15.m_mPlotText: "Who have you fought alongside the longest?"

16.m_mPlotText: "Acappella."

17.m_mPlotText: "I was fighting while she just stood there complaining. Does that count?"

18.m_mPlotText: "...I suppose so."

19.m_mPlotText: "In that case, start with Acappella."

20.m_mPlotText: "I understand, and yet I don't."

21.m_mPlotText: "Anna asked me to thank you."

22.m_mPlotText: "You're welcome."

23.m_mPlotText: "Also, next time… maybe don't let Anna read our letters."

24.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "No."

2.m_mPlotText: "What's wrong?"

3.m_mPlotText: "I received a letter from Acappella. She said you've been unusually warm toward her these days."

4.m_mPlotText: "Her words were full of complaints, but… it didn't seem like she minded."

5.m_mPlotText: "Yes."

6.m_mPlotText: "But that's not right."

7.m_mPlotText: "I've rediscovered a long-lost emotion. Show Acappella attention, watching her complain… it makes me smile."

8.m_mPlotText: "I consulted a dictionary in the library. This feeling is labeled as happiness, or perhaps joy."

9.m_mPlotText: "But it's not what I'm looking for."

10.m_mPlotText: "Is that kind of feeling wrong?"

11.m_mPlotText: "It's acceptable. Just not what I need."

12.m_mPlotText: "According to the dictionary's definitions, what I need… is called sadness."

13.m_mPlotText: "Could the dictionary be wrong?"

14.m_mPlotText: "...So sadness is your reason for fighting?"

15.m_mPlotText: "I've checked every dictionary in the library. They have the same definition."

16.m_mPlotText: "It's the same reason I protect Acappella."

17.m_mPlotText: "When was the last time you felt sadness?"

19.m_mPlotText: "The day Tris adopted me."

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I need paint."

2.m_mPlotText: "You know about art?"

3.m_mPlotText: "What do you need it for?"

4.m_mPlotText: "I understand, and yet I don't."

5.m_mPlotText: "To reclaim sadness."

6.m_mPlotText: "I'm not sure I follow... Can't the Church provide it?"

7.m_mPlotText: "No. The paint is special. It's only available where you are."

8.m_mPlotText: "If the Church doesn't have it, how could I?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Bella."

10.m_mPlotText: "…Elder Bella may reside in Bathory Castle, but generosity isn't exactly her vocation."

11.m_mPlotText: "I'll pay."

12.m_mPlotText: "I purchased the paint from the Puppet Association. It cost quite a fortune."

13.m_mPlotText: "I've got it. When will you come pick it up?"

14.m_mPlotText: "Please deliver it here."

15.m_mPlotText: "I'll cover the delivery fee."

16.m_mPlotText: "And bring my book."

17.m_mPlotText: "(Several days later, a map arrived at the castle. It marked a time and a place—if memory serves, it was where Tris first took Darcias in.)"

1.m_mPlotText: "The paint is ready. It's time to find that girl in silver armor."
"Feuler has brought a letter from the Church."

2.m_mPlotText: "Though I'd like to ignore it, the solemn wax seal and embossed gold lettering on the envelope make it impossible not to feel pressured."

3.m_mPlotText: "Hey there, silver hair."

4.m_mPlotText: "What was your name again?"

5.m_mPlotText: "Oh right, Noah Nevernight."

6.m_mPlotText: "Noah, stop pretending! I know exactly where you're hiding! Reply to my letter!"

7.m_mPlotText: "Reply! Right! Now! Or I'll blow you and your castle sky-high!"

8.m_mPlotText: "Not the person you're looking for."

9.m_mPlotText: "Acknowledged."

10.m_mPlotText: "...Are you serious?"

11.m_mPlotText: "Fine, I'll raid your hideout right now."

12.m_mPlotText: "Get ready to be burned to charcoal."

13.m_mPlotText: "Before we resort to violence, let's discuss why you sent the letter."

14.m_mPlotText: "Hmph..."

15.m_mPlotText: "Are you interrogating me?"

16.m_mPlotText: "Shouldn't you at least show some respect to a Bell Ringer? Especially since you're a Bloodborn Heretic."

17.m_mPlotText: "Most Honorable Bell Ringer, what troubles could have prompted you to grace me with your letter at this late hour?"

18.m_mPlotText: "I didn't ask you to reply with such a nauseating tone!"

19.m_mPlotText: "Please enlighten me, how should a Bloodborn properly show respect to a Bell Ringer?"

20.m_mPlotText: "How should I know!?"

21.m_mPlotText: "Enough! Let's get to the real matter at hand."

22.m_mPlotText: "Aren't you Bloodborn particularly good at playing hide and seek?"

23.m_mPlotText: "...I prefer to call it "counter-surveillance techniques.""

24.m_mPlotText: "Whatever, call it what you like."

25.m_mPlotText: "I need your help with those techniques of yours."

26.m_mPlotText: "I have a rather bad feeling about this."

27.m_mPlotText: "But I'm still curious how you plan to screw me over."

28.m_mPlotText: "Haven't decided yet. Let me think about it."

29.m_mPlotText: "...Then why did you send the letter?"

32.m_mPlotText: "Very well. I'll pay you a personal visit then."

33.m_mPlotText: "I think we should return to a more rational discussion."

35.m_mPlotText: "Now then, I'll have to think carefully about how to persuade you to help me."

36.m_mPlotText: "I'll be sure to write to you again soon."

40.m_mPlotText: "Feuler delivered the last letter, panting heavily."

1.m_mPlotText: "Hey, Noah!"

2.m_mPlotText: "Before today ends—"

3.m_mPlotText: "No, it must be now."

4.m_mPlotText: "Stir up some trouble in a town nearby. Make it look like an attack to the Church."

5.m_mPlotText: "Try to gather as many witnesses as possible."

6.m_mPlotText: "Is the Church about to face an internal war?"

7.m_mPlotText: "The task description isn't clear enough. I need more detailed guidance."

8.m_mPlotText: "Drop it! Just do your job."

9.m_mPlotText: "...You're impossible!"

10.m_mPlotText: "Just scare some guards, slash some statues, or blow something up."

11.m_mPlotText: "Do whatever you want—just don’t hurt anyone."

12.m_mPlotText: "After all, isn't that what you Bloodborn do best? Causing trouble and running away?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Is this what you call "help"?"

14.m_mPlotText: "Yes, absolutely, that's right."

15.m_mPlotText: "Get going! I'm watching, and don't take too long!"

16.m_mPlotText: "Doubtful, Noah did as he was told. But nothing major."

17.m_mPlotText: "Though it doesn't quite match your requirements, consider it done."

18.m_mPlotText: "I heard that."

19.m_mPlotText: "The suspect now requires an explanation from the one who captured him."

20.m_mPlotText: "We'll talk later."

21.m_mPlotText: "After a long while, there was still no reply from Acappella."

22.m_mPlotText: "Late into the night..."

23.m_mPlotText: "Hahaha, it's been so long since I've wandered around outside like this."

24.m_mPlotText: "That was so fun! I'm such a genius!"

25.m_mPlotText: "Noah?"

26.m_mPlotText: "Noah? Are you asleep?"

27.m_mPlotText: "Aren't you Bloodborn supposed to be awake at night?"

28.m_mPlotText: "Noah!"

35.m_mPlotText: "One of us is being unreasonable here, and it's not me."

37.m_mPlotText: "And you're going to keep acting up again."

38.m_mPlotText: "If you still won't explain why, I'm going to bed."

39.m_mPlotText: "You do your part leaving traces, and I'll do mine failing to catch you."

40.m_mPlotText: "The two of us are just playing our little arranged game of cat and mouse."

41.m_mPlotText: "Now I can sneak out for some fresh air whenever I want."

43.m_mPlotText: "You're so good at hiding anyway, and I'm the only one who knows where you go."

45.m_mPlotText: "Of course I am. Why do you ask?"

49.m_mPlotText: "But the price will be getting blown to pieces."

1.m_mPlotText: "We're done for."

2.m_mPlotText: "Noah, we've got a problem."

3.m_mPlotText: "Hey, Noah."

4.m_mPlotText: "I think Darcias found out about us."

5.m_mPlotText: "Am I going to be wanted now?"

6.m_mPlotText: "So she's joining us too?"

7.m_mPlotText: "That's impossible."

8.m_mPlotText: "Quick, help me think of something!"

9.m_mPlotText: "I'm not going to explain this to her. She wouldn't understand anyway."

10.m_mPlotText: "No more pretense. Let's come clean with her."

11.m_mPlotText: "Why don't we silence her for good?"

12.m_mPlotText: "Huh? Have you lost your mind?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Be serious!"

14.m_mPlotText: "This is all quite far from "serious.""

15.m_mPlotText: "Why did it have to be her who figured it out?"

16.m_mPlotText: "Did I overdo it when I was acting upset?"

17.m_mPlotText: "Maybe you were just too happy to notice properly."

18.m_mPlotText: "If our plan gets exposed, that dimwit Darcias will never stop lecturing us."

19.m_mPlotText: "What if she writes a report about us?!"

20.m_mPlotText: "Ugh! This is so frustrating!"

21.m_mPlotText: "If only we could shake her off next time..."

22.m_mPlotText: "Wait... how did I not think of this before!"

23.m_mPlotText: "Let me think about it some more. Just wait for my letter!"

24.m_mPlotText: "You must wait!"

25.m_mPlotText: "You're the most important piece in this plan."

26.m_mPlotText: "Why do I have such an ominous feeling..."

27.m_mPlotText: "Quiet! I'm trying to think!"

28.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Noah."

2.m_mPlotText: "Okay."

3.m_mPlotText: "Our cat and mouse covenant still..."

4.m_mPlotText: "End it right now, correct?"

5.m_mPlotText: "So the time has finally come for us to part ways."

6.m_mPlotText: "No."

7.m_mPlotText: "Our cat and mouse covenant wasn't bold enough."

8.m_mPlotText: "The spectacle wasn't grand enough, the commotion wasn't loud enough!"

10.m_mPlotText: "I'm starting to think you're methodically plotting to murder me."

12.m_mPlotText: "You're clever, but you've got it backwards."

13.m_mPlotText: "It's not me killing you—it's you who's planning to strike me down."

14.m_mPlotText: "(Remaining silent, watching as Acappella's "brilliant plan" unfolds)"

15.m_mPlotText: "Now I know why our plot was exposed."

16.m_mPlotText: "Because it's the same tired plot every time—you leave an opening, and I fail to catch you. The pattern is just too cliché."

17.m_mPlotText: "So what we need is a plot twist!"

18.m_mPlotText: "Next time you're causing trouble out there, I'll descend from the heavens for our fateful duel."

19.m_mPlotText: "But wait!"

20.m_mPlotText: "I'll deliberately leave an opening, and you'll seize that chance to strike me down."

21.m_mPlotText: "I'm curious—how do you think that will play out?"

22.m_mPlotText: "The next step is for you to take me hostage."

23.m_mPlotText: "Then I can finally slip away from Darcias and those stubborn old folks at the Church, and have some peace and quiet for once."

25.m_mPlotText: "Are you speechless in the face of my brilliant scheming?"

26.m_mPlotText: "Hmm, I think I'm about to make history."

27.m_mPlotText: "Quite an honor, isn't it?"

28.m_mPlotText: "How horrible."

30.m_mPlotText: "I'll take you somewhere fun later, I promise."

38.m_mPlotText: "I'll contact you once I figure out the next step."

39.m_mPlotText: "You're finished if you dare leave me waiting here."

1.m_mPlotText: "Noah, I've picked out the perfect spot. You better not blow our cover!"
"This letter was sent by Bathory elders to the Silver-haired guest, with Joyce entrusted as the translator."

2.m_mPlotText: "You stole something important from me, meow."

3.m_mPlotText: "You're... the black cat elder?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Indeed. Joyce's client is none other than the legendary black cat elder. So, do you have enough Soli to make amends for your theft?"

5.m_mPlotText: "I only claimed what my friend had left behind. Can that truly be called theft?"

6.m_mPlotText: "You took it from my nest—my bed. How could that not be theft?"

7.m_mPlotText: "So that cat's nest is important to you... However..."

8.m_mPlotText: "Would a cat under the care of the lavish Matriarch even bother with my meager peace offering?"

9.m_mPlotText: "You've uncovered that as well? Poking around in a cat's secrets isn't very noble, you know."

10.m_mPlotText: "How does a mere cat of the Matriarch survive this long?"

11.m_mPlotText: "Could you have nine lives?"

12.m_mPlotText: "Could you be a Bloodborn among cats?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Is that so? Meow... down to my last tail now."

14.m_mPlotText: "Fangs, mystery, and nocturnal instincts... Maybe all cats are destined to be Bloodborn?"

15.m_mPlotText: "As a reward for your cleverness, how about offering some catnip to your elder?"

16.m_mPlotText: "Guess this reward isn't for me."

17.m_mPlotText: "Remember, it must be from Sapphire Isle."

18.m_mPlotText: "Sapphire Isle... does that place hold special meaning for you?"

19.m_mPlotText: "The catnip of Sapphire Isle alone carries that familiar scent."

20.m_mPlotText: "A blend of salty sea air and Esmeralda's enchanting herbs."

21.m_mPlotText: "No further replies came—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "To the mysterious diviner, what is your connection to the black cat elder of the Bathory family?"

2.m_mPlotText: "What makes you ask that?"

3.m_mPlotText: "It was the omen from the tarot."

4.m_mPlotText: "It's the intuition of a protagonist."

5.m_mPlotText: "It seems you have a gift for divination?"

6.m_mPlotText: "As expected of the Fool chosen by destiny."

7.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps I forgot to introduce myself at the El Dorado—I am Jacintha Dalcarlo."

8.m_mPlotText: "You share the elder's name... Is that black cat in the castle you in another form?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Is that so?"

10.m_mPlotText: "If a ritual could grant you the experience of another life, from beginning to end..."

11.m_mPlotText: "Is that life merely a dream within the ritual? Or is the ritual the reality, and 'you' just a vessel for the life it manifests?"

12.m_mPlotText: "The ritual is but a dream."

13.m_mPlotText: "The ritual is reality."

14.m_mPlotText: "Both are my true life."

15.m_mPlotText: "A life not chosen by me is not mine to claim."

16.m_mPlotText: "What I truly experience becomes my reality."

17.m_mPlotText: "All that I perceive and ponder, be it real or imagined, are etched into my flesh and memory."

18.m_mPlotText: "My dear 'Fool,' this then is my answer to your question."

19.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Now that I know you reside in the castle—when would you like me to return the tarot cards you left in my room?"

2.m_mPlotText: "You may just leave them in my room."

3.m_mPlotText: "I think it's better if I return them in person. After all, you said these tarot cards are very important to you."

4.m_mPlotText: "Is this... an invitation to meet?"

5.m_mPlotText: "I want to see you."

6.m_mPlotText: "I want to see the little black cat."

7.m_mPlotText: "Is it the Fool's pure essence that wins the favor of fate?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Meow? Are you bringing me new catnip?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Could I take that adorable sound as a hint of your nervousness?"

10.m_mPlotText: "We need no plans—the tarot will guide our paths to meet again."

11.m_mPlotText: "And in my vision, that day is close at hand."

12.m_mPlotText: "Should I keep the tarot close, awaiting that day's arrival?"

14.m_mPlotText: "(Perhaps... the tarot will truly guide me to her?)"

15.m_mPlotText: "(Let me try drawing a card.)"

16.m_mPlotText: "(The Moon, reversed.)"

17.m_mPlotText: "(I've never learned to read the tarot... but I might go and see, beneath the guidance of tonight's moonlight.)"

18.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "A gathering's murmur drifts from beyond the castle walls... Could this be the destined encounter that the tarot divination foretold?"
"Among the scattered papers, I found a refund slip from the pharmacy."

2.m_mPlotText: "Issued in the name of "Piera Paracelsus.""

3.m_mPlotText: "Miss Piera, it seems the pharmacy accidentally delivered your refund slip to me."

4.m_mPlotText: "A refund? But I already received all the herbs…"

5.m_mPlotText: "It appears there was a pricing error and you were overcharged."

6.m_mPlotText: "I see... they're more honest than I thought."

7.m_mPlotText: "Are you feeling unwell?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Those herbs are...?"

9.m_mPlotText: "It's nothing. Just a little under the weather."

10.m_mPlotText: "Some ordinary medicinal herbs, that's all."

11.m_mPlotText: "But the refund is… quite substantial. How much did you buy?"

12.m_mPlotText: "Really, it's fine. Just a cold."

13.m_mPlotText: "Some medicine, a bit of rest, and I'll be right as rain."

14.m_mPlotText: "Are you sure you're alright?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Piera?"

16.m_mPlotText: "I waited for a long time. But no reply came."

17.m_mPlotText: "Maybe… she really does need the rest."

1.m_mPlotText: "It's been days since the pharmacy refund slip arrived, and still no word from Piera."

2.m_mPlotText: "Just now, Feuler brought a letter."

3.m_mPlotText: "Mr. Noah, I sincerely apologize!"

4.m_mPlotText: "I've been bedridden these past few days, too weak to write. Please forgive the delay."

5.m_mPlotText: "Are you feeling any better?"

6.m_mPlotText: "Much better, now that I've taken the medicine. I should've taken a proper rest right from the beginning..."

7.m_mPlotText: "But don't worry, I will, once everything is settled."

8.m_mPlotText: "The Church didn't grant you any sick leave?"

9.m_mPlotText: "What could be more important than recovery?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Actually... I've been tending to the bodies of fallen soldiers."

11.m_mPlotText: "So many have died in this war… I couldn't bear to leave them like that."

12.m_mPlotText: "I can help you with that."

13.m_mPlotText: "Noah... this isn't something you should be doing."

14.m_mPlotText: "And… they wouldn't want too many people to see them like that."

15.m_mPlotText: "...You're right, I didn't consider that."

16.m_mPlotText: "However… there is something I might need your help with."

17.m_mPlotText: "Go ahead."

18.m_mPlotText: "Some time ago, I prepared the remains of an unidentified child."

19.m_mPlotText: "It's been many days, and no one has come to claim them."

20.m_mPlotText: "Any identifying features?"

21.m_mPlotText: "The battle was brutal. The body's thin, and badly damaged."

22.m_mPlotText: "But there's a triangular scar—on the right ear. The rest… is unrecognizable."

23.m_mPlotText: "A scar on the right ear. Thin build. I'll remember."

24.m_mPlotText: "I suspect the child enlisted just for a warm meal. But in the end..."

25.m_mPlotText: "Most likely an orphan. Poor child. Such a tragic fate."

26.m_mPlotText: "Yes… Orphans have the loneliest souls. No one to remember them. No one to grieve."

27.m_mPlotText: "Noah… Will I fade away like that someday? Leaving nothing behind?"

30.m_mPlotText: "If I'm buried and forgotten… Who will remember the lives of my mother, my grandmother? Their stories will vanish."

32.m_mPlotText: "I'll find that child's family. I swear it."

33.m_mPlotText: "And when I do… Will you share your family's stories with me too?"

1.m_mPlotText: "Many days had passed since I promised Piera I'd find the child's relatives."

2.m_mPlotText: "But the search… wasn't going well."

3.m_mPlotText: "Noah..."

4.m_mPlotText: "Don't worry, I'm still working on finding that child."

5.m_mPlotText: "It's proving to be quite difficult..."

6.m_mPlotText: "I didn't mean to rush you!"

7.m_mPlotText: "That's not why I wrote… It's something else."

8.m_mPlotText: "Did something happen?"

9.m_mPlotText: "I suppose… it's still related to that child, in a way."

10.m_mPlotText: "Hm?"

11.m_mPlotText: "The sighs... they're getting more distinct."

12.m_mPlotText: "The sighs?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Ever since I was little, I've heard them—Spirits sighing in the dead of night."

14.m_mPlotText: "Sometimes distant, sometimes close... filled with sorrow and resignation."

15.m_mPlotText: "But lately… It's as if they're in the room with me. Whispering right by my ear."

16.m_mPlotText: "Piera… you're under too much stress."

17.m_mPlotText: "You know… many in my family crossed over at my age."

18.m_mPlotText: "Maybe… Maybe they're calling for me."

19.m_mPlotText: "Don't say that. Don't even think it."

20.m_mPlotText: "Huh? I'm not thinking anything dangerous… I just miss them."

21.m_mPlotText: "Lately, I've even started hearing a child's voice among the sighs."

22.m_mPlotText: "Could it be that child?"

23.m_mPlotText: "Maybe."

24.m_mPlotText: "That child... must be lonely too."

25.m_mPlotText: "At least you're still thinking of that child."

26.m_mPlotText: "I'll find their family, I swear it. They won't be forgotten."

27.m_mPlotText: "Yes... But maybe I'm the only one left."

28.m_mPlotText: "Maybe that child has no one else in this world…"

29.m_mPlotText: "I'm sorry. Am I being too pessimistic?"

31.m_mPlotText: "You're right… I think I'm running a fever again. Maybe the sighs were just a fever dream."

32.m_mPlotText: "Thank you… for listening to all this nonsense. I'm… getting tired..."

35.m_mPlotText: "At least for tonight, may her dreams bring her warmth and peace."

1.m_mPlotText: "Piera seemed to have been struggling with her illness for several more days."

2.m_mPlotText: "Even so, the search for the child's family never ceased."

3.m_mPlotText: "Piera, are you feeling any better?"

4.m_mPlotText: "I've expanded the notice area."

5.m_mPlotText: "My contacts are helping gather leads from other sources."

6.m_mPlotText: "Piera did not respond."

7.m_mPlotText: "Take care of yourself. Leave the rest to me."

8.m_mPlotText: "Still, no reply came."

9.m_mPlotText: "(Maybe… she's still asleep.)"

10.m_mPlotText: "Noah!"

11.m_mPlotText: "Noah!!!"

12.m_mPlotText: "Hm?"

13.m_mPlotText: "They're here!!!!"

14.m_mPlotText: "Who's here?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Is it another spirit?"

16.m_mPlotText: "Someone came to claim the child's remains!"

17.m_mPlotText: "No, someone came to claim the child's remains!"

18.m_mPlotText: "That's wonderful news!"

19.m_mPlotText: "So the child was a messenger in the Kingdom's army. The ones who came were his comrades."

20.m_mPlotText: "They even told me stories about him."

21.m_mPlotText: "So he was well-loved?"

22.m_mPlotText: "Yes. He had such a kind heart. Two of them even said they owed their lives to him."

23.m_mPlotText: "But… none of them cried. It was as if the child had just gone off on a long journey—not vanished from this world."

24.m_mPlotText: "Maybe that's because he lived with purpose—"

25.m_mPlotText: "And now, their longing for him runs deep."

26.m_mPlotText: "Noah..."

27.m_mPlotText: "Aha! You've been waiting to say that, haven't you?!"

28.m_mPlotText: "...You got me."

30.m_mPlotText: "None of this would've been possible without you."

35.m_mPlotText: "I'll set everything else aside and focus on recovering properly."

39.m_mPlotText: "I really want to see you, Noah."

40.m_mPlotText: "Sure. But only after you've regained some strength."

41.m_mPlotText: "Then I'll go pick up some new herbs right away!"

1.m_mPlotText: "I'm feeling much better now, Noah... I think I'm ready to see you again."
"A letter arrived from an unknown sender, addressed to "The Stranger from Afar.""

2.m_mPlotText: "Greetings, Stranger."

3.m_mPlotText: "I write this letter because I once heard a maid speak of those who live by the sea, how they place their innermost thoughts in bottles and let the waves carry them to distant shores."

4.m_mPlotText: "And so, I invented an address, sending these untold feelings to the unknown."

5.m_mPlotText: "Today is my birthday. My father has arranged a grand celebration, with renowned Lords and Elders all gathering to mark the occasion."

6.m_mPlotText: "Father announced that I am "the most gifted heir, a once-in-a-century qualified one." His eyes brimmed with expectation."

7.m_mPlotText: "They spent a long time preparing an exquisite "ritual tool" as a gift for me."

8.m_mPlotText: "But I dare not meet his gaze. I don't know—"

9.m_mPlotText: "Is the true protagonist of this celebration really "me," or is it that heir and qualified one who bears all the gazes?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps I'm afraid to know the answer."

11.m_mPlotText: "Happy birthday."

12.m_mPlotText: "Believe this: you are the protagonist of your own world!"

13.m_mPlotText: "No matter what others think, I, a distant stranger, sincerely wish you well."

14.m_mPlotText: "Somewhere in this world—be it in the past, present, or future—there must be many others like me who wish "you" well, too."

15.m_mPlotText: "Thank you!"

16.m_mPlotText: "Not just at celebrations, but in all events in life, we are our own protagonists!"

17.m_mPlotText: "I see... Thank you for your reply."

18.m_mPlotText: "I never imagined that the address I wrote on a whim would actually exist—and even more surprising, that the reply would bring an answer to my confusion."

19.m_mPlotText: "Please think of me as your "birthday fairy godparent.""

20.m_mPlotText: "All I did was offer some personal advice."

21.m_mPlotText: "Not knowing what you like, I found a handcrafted lamb at the market. I'm sending it along with this letter—please accept it as my birthday gift to you."

22.m_mPlotText: "Thank you so much! Actually, lambs are my favorite animals!"

23.m_mPlotText: "We have many lambs in our family's pasture, and I often spend my free time playing with them."

24.m_mPlotText: "This is the first time I've received... a gift I truly love."

25.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps it was fate that guided me to write this letter, and fate that brought it to you."

26.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "A month later, I received another letter from that mysterious address."

2.m_mPlotText: "Hello, distant stranger."

3.m_mPlotText: "It's been a while since my last letter. Another birthday has come around for me—I hope you're doing well."

4.m_mPlotText: "Your birthday came and went so quickly."

5.m_mPlotText: "Happy birthday."

6.m_mPlotText: "Is this some kind of new scam?"

7.m_mPlotText: "Eh? Having a birthday once a year... isn't that perfectly normal?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Thank you!"

9.m_mPlotText: "I'm so relieved that your address hasn't changed."

10.m_mPlotText: "At my birthday banquet this year, father and the Elders spoke of many mysterious things... They said someone could finally inherit the family's mission, and mentioned taking me to a "ritual." I don't understand what they mean."

11.m_mPlotText: "Father was in high spirits and had a few extra drinks at the banquet. In his drunken state, he led me to the forbidden grounds."

12.m_mPlotText: "A stench from the Abyss permeated the cold dungeon—there was actually a monster in the forbidden grounds."

13.m_mPlotText: "Father opened the iron doors one by one, then sat beside the monster, endlessly mumbling to himself as both smiles and tears crept across his face."

14.m_mPlotText: "The monster had slender limbs and a hoarse voice. On its wrinkled, festering face, one could barely make out features that seemed almost human."

15.m_mPlotText: "I asked father what the monster was, but he remained silent."

16.m_mPlotText: "It seems your father harbors deep feelings for the monster."

17.m_mPlotText: "It seems your father harbors deep hatred for the monster."

18.m_mPlotText: "I don't know... I'm afraid the monster might harm him."

19.m_mPlotText: "I fear for my own future as well, wondering if I too will become a monster imprisoned by the family's mission."

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "In the Lupine Forest, I accidentally entered the Ganelon family's forbidden grounds, where I unexpectedly encountered another Aiona..."
"Much time had passed when, one casual afternoon, I received another letter from afar."

2.m_mPlotText: "Hello, distant stranger."

3.m_mPlotText: "Time has flown by and much has happened. I don't know if you're well, nor if your address has changed."

4.m_mPlotText: "For a time, I forgot—just briefly—that you had once been there to listen to my troubles and guide me through them."

5.m_mPlotText: "I have always been here."

6.m_mPlotText: "This makes me so sad."

7.m_mPlotText: "Thank you!"

8.m_mPlotText: "I apologize, and thank you for still writing to me."

9.m_mPlotText: "Many things happened in my life... and I met some truly wonderful friends."

10.m_mPlotText: "We traveled, studied, and trained together. We promised to watch each other's back, and vowed to fulfill our family's mission together."

11.m_mPlotText: "But finally... we had to take different paths."

12.m_mPlotText: "Not just old friends, but even my father and the elders have left me forever..."

13.m_mPlotText: "You must have gone through difficult times."

14.m_mPlotText: "I was depressed for a while, but recently, I met some new friends."

15.m_mPlotText: "But I don't know if I should accept her kindness."

16.m_mPlotText: "I'm afraid that separation is inevitable. Perhaps I shouldn’t begin at all."

17.m_mPlotText: "You should accept this new friend."

18.m_mPlotText: "The answer already lies in your heart."

19.m_mPlotText: "Time flows forward, and life must move with it."

20.m_mPlotText: "Your hesitation proves that deep down, you already want to be her friend."

21.m_mPlotText: "I can give you a gentle push, but only you can decide by looking into your heart."

22.m_mPlotText: "I see..."

23.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "You know I've been waiting for your reply, right? It's been so long—have you still not found the earring's trace in the memories of my blood?"

2.m_mPlotText: "Not yet."

3.m_mPlotText: "Was that child's name Earring?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Hey, are you actually helping me look for it?"

5.m_mPlotText: "Wait... don't tell me you're watching my memories from my birth?"

6.m_mPlotText: "Why did you ask me to help find your earring? You even gave me your blood."

7.m_mPlotText: "Because you're the only one I trust. And since I'm the last Moonblessed, you're counting on me to recover your memories, aren't you?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Is that earring connected to the baby found on the battlefield?"

9.m_mPlotText: "To be honest, that's where I first met the earring's original owner."

10.m_mPlotText: "As "War", it was indeed war that sang you a lullaby."

11.m_mPlotText: "Everyone has their own cradle at birth. Mine just happened to be that kind of place."

12.m_mPlotText: "Alright, now that your curiosity's satisfied, help me find that earring."

13.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I wonder what memories of mine you've seen this time?"

2.m_mPlotText: "Those weren't your memories."

3.m_mPlotText: "Hey, is that your excuse for not finding the earring?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Everything I saw wasn't through your eyes, but from the height of an earlobe."

5.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps I should be more direct—I've been viewing your past through the perspective of that earring."

6.m_mPlotText: "Moreover, this earring was given to you by a girl in your memories."

7.m_mPlotText: "Your insight is frighteningly sharp..."

8.m_mPlotText: "That girl, you mean the Carrelle family's young princess? She always said I was different from other slaves, and would secretly sneak away to see me."

9.m_mPlotText: "Without her, I probably wouldn't have had the resolve to win that duel."

10.m_mPlotText: "A duel?"

11.m_mPlotText: "Haven't you seen that memory yet? Most slaves kept by the Carrelle family were sent to the arena to fight to the death, entertaining nobles who thirst for thrill."

12.m_mPlotText: "The losers had only one fate—I'm sure you can guess what that was. As for the slave who emerged victorious... their prize was being granted a surname."

13.m_mPlotText: "So that's the origin of Brennholt?"

14.m_mPlotText: "Doesn't sound like much of a prize."

15.m_mPlotText: "Back then, I thought earning a surname meant I could stand by that young princess's side. In the end, it was just another deception."

16.m_mPlotText: "Freedom is worth more than money. But I never expected this surname would be the beginning of yet another deception."

17.m_mPlotText: "The rest is up to you to discover. Don't forget to let me know if you find out what happened to the earring."

18.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Hey, you haven't forgotten about me, have you? Or perhaps you've made some interesting discoveries in those memories?"

2.m_mPlotText: "We're the same, both keeping our promises."

3.m_mPlotText: "I melted in the flames. Found nothing."

4.m_mPlotText: "Unfortunately, I'm the only one left who can keep the promise now."

5.m_mPlotText: "Now that's just cruel. I distinctly remember holding that earring in my hand after the flames died down."

6.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps once I learn what happened back then, I'll be able to find where the earring is."

7.m_mPlotText: "That really puts me in a difficult position. Where should I begin..."

8.m_mPlotText: "Shortly after earning the surname Brennholt, I was taken to the Heart of the Divine Body."

9.m_mPlotText: "To keep the Heart of the Divine Body beating, they needed plenty of fuel to burn—and that's what we, the victorious slaves, were for."

10.m_mPlotText: "They pushed you into the Divine Body to generate enough energy to suppress the Calamity."
