11.m_mPlotText: "I guess I got lucky. When I made contact with the Divine Body, not only did the Calamity "War" break free from its seal, but it also chose my body as its vessel for escape."

12.m_mPlotText: "But you still seem to be the same Agares as before, not "War.""

13.m_mPlotText: "Coincidentally, when it tried to possess my body, I heard another heartbeat inside the Divine Body."

14.m_mPlotText: "That voice helped me regain myself, and I even managed to devour "War" and be reborn in the flames."

15.m_mPlotText: "So that means the heartbeat was coming from within the earring."

16.m_mPlotText: "And what you really wanted me to find wasn't the earring itself, but one behind that heartbeat."

17.m_mPlotText: "Figured it out, have you? You've really got sharp insight!"

18.m_mPlotText: "I don't remember much after being reborn from the Divine Body and losing that earring. Don't keep me waiting so long!"

19.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "A few days after I sent my findings to Agares, a reply appeared on my desk."

2.m_mPlotText: "So that's your conclusion? The earring is with its original owner."

3.m_mPlotText: "That's the most logical deduction."

4.m_mPlotText: "Oh? What if I told you that its original owner—the princess of the Carrelle family—also perished in the Divine Body? Would you still maintain that conclusion?"

5.m_mPlotText: "I stand by it."

6.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps she was resurrected as well."

7.m_mPlotText: "Care to tell me what makes you so certain?"

8.m_mPlotText: "I never expected someone as meticulous as you to have moments of such naivety."

9.m_mPlotText: "The other heartbeat you heard in the flames of the Divine Body is proof that she's still alive."

10.m_mPlotText: "If that were true, she would have had no reason to stay hidden when I launched my war against the Carrelle family."

11.m_mPlotText: "Or perhaps she had the same intentions as you from the beginning."

12.m_mPlotText: "Through the war, you buried the Carrelle family in ruins and built a new order on top of it—exactly what the Carrelle princess intended to do."

13.m_mPlotText: "How do you know?"

14.m_mPlotText: "I heard it myself."

15.m_mPlotText: "Whether it was when you were the chancellor or later when you became the Bell Ringer, that princess never left your side."

16.m_mPlotText: "Don't you think that's a rather frightening thing to say?"

17.m_mPlotText: "The memories I saw belong neither to you nor the earring, but to the princess of the Carrelle family."

18.m_mPlotText: "As for that person's current whereabouts, you probably know better than I do—after all, only one person could be this close to you."

19.m_mPlotText: "Now that you mention it, I might actually know someone like that... Perfect timing, it's been a while since I've had a proper chat with her."

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies. It seemed he had left for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "In the forest bathed in silvery moonlight, I saw Agares, who had been waiting, raise his wine glass to me."

"Dear Sir/Madam,

I trust this letter finds you well. I'm writing to seek your assistance in procuring an organ for the Church choir. The instrument must be capable of perfectly rendering pieces in G minor. Should you know of such an instrument's whereabouts, I would be most grateful if you could inform me of its value.

This matter is of utmost importance, and I earnestly seek your aid. Your favorable response would be met with profound gratitude.

I await your reply with sincere anticipation.

Yours faithfully, Anna"

2.m_mPlotText: "(How strange... why would a letter about an organ for the Church choir be delivered to the castle?)"

3.m_mPlotText: "Ma'am, I apologize for the interruption, but I'm afraid I don't have the instrument you seek."

4.m_mPlotText: "However, if you wish, I could inquire with the castle steward about this matter."

5.m_mPlotText: "Ah... my sincerest apologies. My name is Tris. I'm tasked with finding an organ for the hymn recital."

6.m_mPlotText: "I asked Anna to write that letter. It seems she wrote the wrong address."

7.m_mPlotText: "This child... always so careless. It seems someone needs a little scolding."

8.m_mPlotText: "Child... scolding...? If I’m not mistaken, the letter's from an older person?"

9.m_mPlotText: "You're quite observant. And yes, I suppose 'senior' is accurate enough."

10.m_mPlotText: "But in my eyes, she'll always be that new little girl to the choir, who couldn't resist sneaking a crumb of communion during mass."

11.m_mPlotText: "How time flies... In the blink of an eye, more than sixty years have passed."

12.m_mPlotText: "Still, I must thank you. May the beautiful melodies of the hymns bless your kind soul, always."

13.m_mPlotText: "Please just call me Noah."

14.m_mPlotText: "No further replies came—for now."

15.m_mPlotText: "(Over sixty years ago? That would make Anna at least seventy now. And this lady, Tris... just how old might she be...? Well, a lady’s age truly is an eternal mystery.)"

1.m_mPlotText:
"Greetings,

I am writing to relay the Commander's exact words:

The hymn recital is approaching, and we will need an organ capable of perfectly rendering pieces in G minor. The price is negotiable.

<s>Heaven, is that blood on you? Come here, remove your armor so I can check. Still taking notes? You don’t need to include every word in the letter. Oh, you sweet little perfectionist.</s>

Sincerely,
Darcias"

2.m_mPlotText: "(Another letter from the choir. I should let Tris know about this.)"

3.m_mPlotText: "Is that you, Tris? It seems your assistant sent the letter to the wrong address again."

4.m_mPlotText: "I'm so sorry, Noah. I don't understand how this happened... I even had Darcias handle the mail this time."

5.m_mPlotText: "How strange. She's always been the most reliable one in the choir."

6.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps it's this very meticulousness that has her fixate too much on the details."

7.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps you could try delivering the letters yourself."

8.m_mPlotText: "Indeed, that’s what makes her so endearing. She puts her whole heart into everything she does."

9.m_mPlotText: "Everyone's been busy preparing for the hymn recital, so a few mistakes are bound to happen. I'll deliver it myself tomorrow."

10.m_mPlotText: "Well... even the endearing ones need a bit of guidance when they make mistakes."

11.m_mPlotText: "Speaking of which, there are three stacks of ancient scores waiting to be transcribed in the attic. Perfect for helping Darcias… clear her mind. A thoughtful arrangement, wouldn't you say, Noah?"

12.m_mPlotText: "(Such gentle words, yet they send a chill down my spine...)"

13.m_mPlotText: "Has Darcias recovered yet? Please give her my regards."

14.m_mPlotText: "Eh? How do you know about her injury?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Did she… actually end up including our conversation in the letter after all?"

16.m_mPlotText: "I'm afraid so."

17.m_mPlotText: "I didn't expect you to be so observant."

18.m_mPlotText: "Don't worry, I've already checked for her. It was just a bit of paint."

19.m_mPlotText: "Your warning is timely. I'll need to go through all the other letters that child has handled."

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "After the previous two, on the third day I received another letter from Tris."

2.m_mPlotText: "I apologize for troubling you again, Noah. I've double-checked the address—it is indeed the Twilight Citadel in The Howling Peninsula."

3.m_mPlotText: "How odd. Sir Gadric was quite certain when he gave me the address, assuring me that the organ could be purchased through the local merchant association."

4.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps you're looking for Elder Bella of the Puppet Association?"

5.m_mPlotText: "Ah, yes! That's the name Sir Gadric mentioned. It's my fault—I always forget to write down the recipient."

6.m_mPlotText: "I suddenly feel sorry for Anna and Darcias."

7.m_mPlotText: "Don't worry, I'll make them some puddings to cheer them up right away. And I'll watch them eat every last bite. If that's not enough... they can join me for organ practice in the chapel until dawn. How does that sound?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Wait... the Twilight Citadel, Elder Bella... could this be the castle of the Bathory family?"

10.m_mPlotText: "No."

11.m_mPlotText: "Is there still time for me to run away?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Did I scare you?"

14.m_mPlotText: "I ask only out of curiosity—this is the first time I have ever requested assistance from the Bloodborn, as a Bell Ringer."

15.m_mPlotText: "A Bell Ringer personally running an errand for the organ… The hymn recital must be of great importance to the Church."

16.m_mPlotText: "This isn't just about the Church gathering—it's also a rare opportunity for the children in the choir to shine."

17.m_mPlotText: "Because their parents are heretics, these children have rotten apples thrown at them in the streets, and people tamper with their instrument cases when they perform. Only in the choir can they hold their heads high and sing."

18.m_mPlotText: "But choosing a new organ was entirely my idea. The Church's organ may be seasoned, but it's still functional."

19.m_mPlotText: "Noah, would you ask Elder Bella if she can find an organ perfect for playing in G minor? And if anyone asks what it's for, please keep it a secret."

20.m_mPlotText: "Rest assured. I won't tell a soul."

21.m_mPlotText: "No further replies came—for now."

22.m_mPlotText: "(What could Tris be hiding? No... perhaps it's best not to pry. I should just go find Elder Bella.)"

1.m_mPlotText: "(I consulted Elder Bella about the organ. There are several available, but none in stock that meets Tris's requirement for 'perfect G minor resonance.')"

2.m_mPlotText: "Tris, I spoke with Elder Bella about the organ, but I'm afraid it might be difficult to fulfill your request."

3.m_mPlotText: "I suppose I was being too idealistic. Still, I'm truly grateful for your help, Noah."

4.m_mPlotText: "Please don't say that. Elder Bella mentioned a retired instrument maker who might be able to craft one to order. I can inquire about that for you."

5.m_mPlotText: "I couldn't help but wonder—why the particular emphasis on G minor resonance? It doesn't seem to be a usual priority when selecting an organ."

6.m_mPlotText: "If you found a pearl buried in the sand… what would you do with it?"

7.m_mPlotText: "I would explore its full potential."

8.m_mPlotText: "I'd find the perfect place for it."

9.m_mPlotText: "I feel the same way, Noah. Actually... this organ is meant for a child named Acappella. I apologize for keeping this from you."

10.m_mPlotText: "She's a child with extraordinary musical talent, but the Church refuses to take her in for certain reasons. I couldn't bear to see such talent go to waste, so I secretly arranged for her to perform a solo at the hymn recital."

11.m_mPlotText: "Any musician knows how challenging G minor can be. And to let that talent shine, we need the right instrument."

12.m_mPlotText: "However, I would completely understand if you choose not to be involved with the Church."

13.m_mPlotText: "I don't see a Bell Ringer in front of me—I see a teacher who wants the best for her student. I'll help."

14.m_mPlotText: "Noah... I don’t know how to put it into words, but meeting you must be Aeon's will."

15.m_mPlotText: "After much trouble, I finally found an organ that can perfectly play in G minor. Now I can fulfill Tris's wish."

16.m_mPlotText: "The organ has been assembled. Thank you again for your kindness, Noah. Tomorrow's recital is not public, but I've reserved a seat for you. Please do come and listen."

17.m_mPlotText: "Also... there's something I'd like to tell you. I hope to see you tomorrow, okay?"

18.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "At Tris's invitation, I nervously came to the church, only to find the atmosphere far less hostile than I had expected..."
"An unclaimed letter, or perhaps, a diary?"

2.m_mPlotText: "(Is this just a prank, or...)"

3.m_mPlotText: "(Maybe I should read what's inside? My apologies if I'm being intrusive.)"

4.m_mPlotText: "(These are... memories with Ressa?)"

5.m_mPlotText: "This time, Ressa was more dedicated than ever, spending several days sleeping among piles of books."

6.m_mPlotText: "It seems the fact that I memorized in half a day what took her three years has hit her hard."

7.m_mPlotText: "I hope this motivates her to achieve her dream of becoming a good doctor."

8.m_mPlotText: "(Did something like this happen between Ressa and me? To be honest, I don't remember...)"

9.m_mPlotText: "(But the way this is written—it really does sound like me.)"

10.m_mPlotText: "(What happened next? Let's keep reading...)"

11.m_mPlotText: "We finally found the rare herbs for Ressa's formula on the east side of the island."

12.m_mPlotText: "Maybe that patient could be saved."

13.m_mPlotText: "(This… I think I remember this. And if I'm not mistaken, that patient later...)"

14.m_mPlotText: "His condition worsened. Unfortunately, we couldn't save him."

15.m_mPlotText: "His illness was incurable from the start. No one was to blame."

16.m_mPlotText: "But Ressa didn't see it that way. She wanted to eliminate "death" from the world."

17.m_mPlotText: ""That's impossible." I kept these words to myself, silently staying by her side as she grieved."

18.m_mPlotText: ""If I had caught his illness earlier, if we had tried a different treatment..." Ressa voiced countless "ifs.""

19.m_mPlotText: ""If he had never been born, he wouldn't have died." I couldn't help myself—perhaps I shouldn't have said that, as Ressa's expression grew even darker."

20.m_mPlotText: ""You're right, this is the only way... if...""

21.m_mPlotText: "What did she realize? If what? If we could change the patient's life from the very beginning?"

22.m_mPlotText: "But something like that... We couldn't have known ahead of time, and we certainly can't go back to the past."

23.m_mPlotText: "(That's it?)"

24.m_mPlotText: "(If this is a prank... it's way too immersive. It feels like something I actually experienced one day in the past.)"

25.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "A nameless letter quietly waits on the desk, unopened."

2.m_mPlotText: "A letter from the future... could something like this even work?"

3.m_mPlotText: "But if Empousa is so enthusiastic about it, and even someone as cautious as Aiona thinks I should try... I suppose I might as well give it a shot."

4.m_mPlotText: "(Once again, a letter in handwriting identical to my own.)"

5.m_mPlotText: "So, to my past self, if you are reading this letter, there's something I need to tell you."

6.m_mPlotText: "(How can Feuler suddenly detect the sender's location? And this "past self"... is that referring to me? Is he really my future self?)"

7.m_mPlotText: "Who are you?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Is this Noah?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Words suddenly appeared on the paper. It seems like it worked."

10.m_mPlotText: "Greetings, Noah Nevernight."

11.m_mPlotText: "I never thought this experimental attempt would actually work..."

12.m_mPlotText: "Hello, my past self."

13.m_mPlotText: "So, does this letter really come from the future?"

14.m_mPlotText: "The incident you wrote about—breaking Cain's wine—it actually happened."

15.m_mPlotText: "Empousa and Aiona used some of the Alita family's abilities to make this connection possible, though it seems unstable."

16.m_mPlotText: "That's why it took until now for us to finally establish contact."

17.m_mPlotText: "So, the journal I found earlier—was that yours?"

18.m_mPlotText: "It's mine, and it's yours—after all, we share the same past."

19.m_mPlotText: "However, you'll only be able to remember what's in that diary once you recover all of your past memories."

20.m_mPlotText: "I know you want to change the future—that's why I sent you this letter."

21.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Once again, the mysterious letter appears on the table."

2.m_mPlotText: "Another letter from you."

3.m_mPlotText: "It seems the letter has successfully reached you once more."

4.m_mPlotText: "That's good. So, can you tell me about what happens in the future?"

5.m_mPlotText: "Yes."

6.m_mPlotText: "Huh? I thought you would refuse."

7.m_mPlotText: "Most fantasy stories say the future is something that can't—or shouldn't—be known."

8.m_mPlotText: "That's true."

9.m_mPlotText: "But I'm curious—if you knew the future and chose a different path, would that future change?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Would it change for the better?"

11.m_mPlotText: "Would it change for the worse?"

12.m_mPlotText: "That would be a future even I cannot predict."

13.m_mPlotText: "In that case, let's start with something small."

14.m_mPlotText: "Speaking of which, a week from now, you'll face a battle."

15.m_mPlotText: "So soon... Will it be a battle I'm destined to lose?"

16.m_mPlotText: "No, you won. But your triumph turned to tragedy when you fell from a cliff after your victory."

17.m_mPlotText: "Is this where my life comes to an end?"

18.m_mPlotText: "Not quite. After all, this isn't your first time falling off a cliff, is it? Though it'll hurt."

19.m_mPlotText: "Fortunately, Aunt Mary found you quickly and immediately went to get Aiona."

20.m_mPlotText: "I'll have to thank Mary for that. I remember her—she lives in the village outside the castle."

21.m_mPlotText: "Her apples are some of the sweetest blood substitutes for the Bloodborn."

22.m_mPlotText: "If I'm not mistaken, Cain also uses her grapes to make wine."

23.m_mPlotText: "Over the next few days, she was so devoted to taking care of your injuries that she missed the perfect timing for the grape harvest."

24.m_mPlotText: "This could affect her entire year. If possible, I'd rather not trouble her over something like this."

25.m_mPlotText: "Now let's see if you can change such a small thing after knowing this "future" in advance."

26.m_mPlotText: "We'll talk in a week."

27.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "The correspondence resumes once more."

2.m_mPlotText: "The attempt was both a success and a failure."

3.m_mPlotText: "The fall changed, but the result didn't seem to."

4.m_mPlotText: "I know, since your memories appear in my mind as well."

5.m_mPlotText: "But it's too soon to conclude that "the future is predetermined" based on a single setback."

6.m_mPlotText: "Should I say this is truly worthy of "me"?"

7.m_mPlotText: "It seems you've made many similar attempts before."

8.m_mPlotText: "Would you help me with something?"

9.m_mPlotText: "You mean something that would change my future and your past?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Do you remember Aunt Mary?"

11.m_mPlotText: "The kindhearted woman who cared for "us" in your world? In mine, I haven’t met her, but I still know her."

12.m_mPlotText: "What happened to her?"

13.m_mPlotText: "In a few days, her home will be attacked by a group of bandits."

14.m_mPlotText: "Is this because of the future I changed?"

15.m_mPlotText: "If I had fallen that day and she had taken care of me in the castle, would this have been prevented?"

16.m_mPlotText: "In my world, I did fall and she did take care of me, but this still happened to her."

17.m_mPlotText: "So your fall from the cliff didn't affect her fate. There's no need to blame yourself in this place."

18.m_mPlotText: "What should I do then? Fight off the bandits for her?"

19.m_mPlotText: "No, you must do nothing. You absolutely cannot interfere in this conflict."

20.m_mPlotText: "Then why tell me about it?"

21.m_mPlotText: "Because no matter what, you'll find out. And when you do, you'll rush to her aid without hesitation, because…"

22.m_mPlotText: "—because you've experienced it before. That's why you're telling me now—to stop me from getting involved when the time comes."

23.m_mPlotText: "I think you understand my choice. After all, you know yourself better than anyone."

24.m_mPlotText: "I trust my judgment."

25.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I did exactly what the other Noah told me to do, but the result seems..."
"Van Helsing, did you receive a strange invitation recently?"

2.m_mPlotText: "Invitation? I haven't been at the castle lately. Even if it arrived, I wouldn't have seen it."

3.m_mPlotText: "When did you leave? Why wasn't I informed?"

4.m_mPlotText: "My schedule runs opposite to you Bloodborn. It's only natural you wouldn't notice."

5.m_mPlotText: "So you're off solving another case?"

6.m_mPlotText: "Nothing particularly fascinating. But someone asked, so I must follow through."

7.m_mPlotText: "Well, this invitation to us also involves a case."

8.m_mPlotText: "Us?"

9.m_mPlotText: "You and me."

10.m_mPlotText: "Though you're not here."

11.m_mPlotText: "Interesting."

12.m_mPlotText: "I can still solve cases remotely."

13.m_mPlotText: "Tell me about it."

14.m_mPlotText: "It's an invitation to investigate a mysterious incident at Duke Reese's castle—scheduled for the day after tomorrow."

15.m_mPlotText: "But if you're not coming, perhaps I should decline..."

16.m_mPlotText: "Then I'll leave it to you."

17.m_mPlotText: "Hmm?"

18.m_mPlotText: "I may not be there in person—but you are. We can work through letters."

19.m_mPlotText: "All right."

20.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I've arrived at the castle. Something feels… off."

2.m_mPlotText: "Give me details. What's off?"

3.m_mPlotText: "The Duke lies gravely ill. The servants are silent—too silent—and the air hangs thick with decay. There's a suffocating sense of death."

4.m_mPlotText: "And the invitation?"

5.m_mPlotText: "It came from Duke Reese's son—Reese II."

6.m_mPlotText: "A noble estate, a dying patriarch, a young heir... This must be an inheritance dispute—or a hidden woman."

7.m_mPlotText: "You're half right."

8.m_mPlotText: "Your detective instincts are still sharp."

9.m_mPlotText: "How so?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Thanks for the compliment."

11.m_mPlotText: "There was a woman… but she died five years ago."

12.m_mPlotText: "A dead woman. A strange castle. I assume the place is haunted? Was she the Duke's wife? Or Reese II's?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Good guess. But she is no one's wife."

14.m_mPlotText: "The Duke's wife died in childbirth. Reese II has never married."

15.m_mPlotText: "The house is haunted by a former maid. They say her spirit appears at night, endlessly washing laundry."

16.m_mPlotText: "Because of this, the Duke's condition has grown worse."

17.m_mPlotText: "Is this why we were invited...?"

18.m_mPlotText: "How did the maid die?"

19.m_mPlotText: "No one will say. The entire castle is keeping secrets—even Reese II."

20.m_mPlotText: "Then investigate carefully. And… thank you for the effort."

21.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I conducted an investigation at Duke Reese's castle, but the servants are highly vigilant and little was discovered."

2.m_mPlotText: "That makes it even more suspicious."

3.m_mPlotText: "This ghost—they didn't just imagine her."

4.m_mPlotText: "You saw it?"

5.m_mPlotText: "You could say that. A figure was there, washing laundry. But when I rushed in, it vanished."

6.m_mPlotText: "Interesting. What else?"

7.m_mPlotText: "I ran into a servant that same night—he was also watching the ghost."

8.m_mPlotText: "Did you interrogate him?"

9.m_mPlotText: "...what exactly have I done to give you that impression?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Aren’t you the one who prefers aggressive methods?"

11.m_mPlotText: "I'm sure you must have uncovered some inside information?"

12.m_mPlotText: "He told me what he knew. Willingly."

13.m_mPlotText: "Hilda came to the Reese estate with her mother as a child. She used to serve Duke Reese and grew up alongside Reese II."

14.m_mPlotText: "Rumors swirled about the two of them… until Reese II became engaged to someone else."

15.m_mPlotText: "Later, the maid died, so the rumors stopped naturally."

16.m_mPlotText: "Yes. They say she hanged herself. Out of heartbreak… or abandonment."

17.m_mPlotText: "But the servant doesn't believe it was suicide."

18.m_mPlotText: "Why?"

19.m_mPlotText: "Hilda was cheerful. She spoke of starting over elsewhere."

20.m_mPlotText: "And more importantly—no one ever saw her body. Only Reese II claimed to have seen it."

21.m_mPlotText: "That would make him our prime suspect."

22.m_mPlotText: "No. There's someone else."

23.m_mPlotText: "The cook."

24.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Have you identified any suspects in the Reese case?"

2.m_mPlotText: "I went to question the cook."

3.m_mPlotText: "Did you truly questioned her? Or did you say "You're now a prime suspect. Better spill the beans.""

4.m_mPlotText: "It was civil. And besides, I learned those tactics from you."

5.m_mPlotText: "And?"

6.m_mPlotText: "The cook is harsh, but not as cruel as I imagined."

7.m_mPlotText: "She admitted treating Hilda poorly… but when she found out Hilda was pregnant, she actually tried to comfort her."

8.m_mPlotText: "Pregnant? A woman with her temperament and faith—suicide doesn't add up."

9.m_mPlotText: "That's what everyone thinks..."

10.m_mPlotText: "Who do you suspect?"

11.m_mPlotText: "I still find the cook suspicious."

12.m_mPlotText: "The servant. He seems shifty."

13.m_mPlotText: "I suspect it's Reese II."

14.m_mPlotText: "Reasonable."

15.m_mPlotText: "They claim Hilda left a note—but it's locked in the family study."

16.m_mPlotText: "Time to put those Bloodborn eyes to use. Check the study tonight."

17.m_mPlotText: "No further replies came—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Under cover of night, I sneaked into Duke Reese's study, only to discover something entirely unexpected..."
"Thanks for helping me out earlier! If it weren't for you, who knows how long I would've been lying there!"

2.m_mPlotText: "Next time you go out, let us know first."

3.m_mPlotText: "If you're planning to sleep outside again, at least bring a blanket."

4.m_mPlotText: "Alright, I'm sorry! It all happened so fast, and I had to rush to deal with it."

5.m_mPlotText: "You have a point... Wait, no! I wasn't just sleeping somewhere random—I went there because it was urgent!"

6.m_mPlotText: "If those alchemists hadn't barged into the sealed area, I wouldn't have had to leave in such a hurry."

7.m_mPlotText: "But you're seriously incredible! You took down all those alchemists on your own!"

8.m_mPlotText: "Even though they weren't much in combat, they had all sorts of strange potions and tools. I'd have probably been in serious trouble."

9.m_mPlotText: "I didn't do anything."

10.m_mPlotText: "...Huh? If it wasn't you, then who? When I woke up, it was just the two of us there!"

11.m_mPlotText: "By the time I arrived, they were all dead. One clean strike for each."

12.m_mPlotText: "What…? Could someone else be helping me?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps there are still survivors of the Ganelon family in Mouret."

14.m_mPlotText: "I've looked into it—since the family migrated from Lupine Forest, they never came back."

15.m_mPlotText: "But if it wasn't them, who else would know about the forbidden grounds... Ah! Could it be... Clive Jr.?"

16.m_mPlotText: "I need to head to Lupine Forest right away! If he's back, I have to find him!"

17.m_mPlotText: "There's no response. She must be investigating."

1.m_mPlotText: "I can't figure this out on my own! Noah, help me think—who else could it be?"

2.m_mPlotText: "Besides Clive and Gadric, who else knows you?"

3.m_mPlotText: "That only leaves the people from Mouret... Wait, could it be their spirits protecting me?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Spirits wouldn't leave wounds like that."

5.m_mPlotText: "That's quite possible."

6.m_mPlotText: "You're right... If spirits were real, they'd probably show up when I'm awake, right? I mean, they'd have plenty to say to me."

7.m_mPlotText: "It's the only explanation that makes sense... Wait, you're not just saying that to make me feel better, are you?"

8.m_mPlotText: "But why would they leave the message "don't look for me"? Are they avoiding me?"

9.m_mPlotText: "It‘s more likely that, for some reason, they can’t show themselves."

10.m_mPlotText: "They're standing right behind you."

11.m_mPlotText: "But if they've helped me out of trouble twice already, why won't they just let me meet them?"

12.m_mPlotText: "Eek—! How did you know... Wait, there's no one behind me!"

13.m_mPlotText: "Still, every time they show up, it's when you're unconscious. That might have something to do with it."

14.m_mPlotText: "Unconscious... but I can't exactly knock myself out, can I?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Those alchemists won't give up so easily on the mushrooms in the forbidden grounds."

16.m_mPlotText: "I get it!"

17.m_mPlotText: "If I pretend to faint when I meet them, then I can see who's been saving me, right? I'll go prepare right away!"

18.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "You shouldn't have given Hati that idea."

2.m_mPlotText: "Who are you? Why are you messaging me under Hati's name?"

3.m_mPlotText: "Hati is smarter than we thought."

4.m_mPlotText: "I am Hati, and yet I am not Hati."

5.m_mPlotText: "You seem to know exactly who I am."

6.m_mPlotText: ""Plague" Sheila—the first Moonblessed of the Apocalypse I've been searching for. I guess I wasn't wrong."

7.m_mPlotText: "Your insight is impressive. In that case, maybe you can understand why I reached out to you…"

8.m_mPlotText: "—To keep my existence hidden from Hati."

9.m_mPlotText: "If she learns that I'm still conscious, it'll only cause her more pain."

10.m_mPlotText: "All I know is that she risked her life just to thank you, her "Guardian.""

11.m_mPlotText: "As her "other half," it's only right that I protect her. And besides… she's my sister. I could never abandon her."

12.m_mPlotText: "I am not the "Plague." I'm speaking to you as family, asking you to keep this from her."

13.m_mPlotText: "Hati might seem reckless most of the time, but deep down, she's far more sensitive than she lets on."

14.m_mPlotText: "As the force that runs through her veins, you can hide this from everyone—except her."

15.m_mPlotText: "So... can you promise me you won't tell her about this conversation?"

16.m_mPlotText: "That is, if she doesn't ask about it."

17.m_mPlotText: "There has been no new response from them."

1.m_mPlotText: "Not long after meeting Hati, I received another letter from her."

2.m_mPlotText: "I've figured out how to talk to him!"

3.m_mPlotText: "Are you asking me to deliver a message for you?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Clean your room first."

5.m_mPlotText: "As expected of you, already knowing what I was going to ask before I even said it!"

6.m_mPlotText: "That's not important right now. Listen to me first—"

7.m_mPlotText: "Lately, there've been a lot of people sent by the Church snooping around the forbidden grounds. The alchemists must have told them about me."

8.m_mPlotText: "If I pretend to be surrounded by Church forces, he will surely appear to help me. That's when you'll get your chance to talk to him!"

9.m_mPlotText: "This could be dangerous."

10.m_mPlotText: "I'm sure you'll keep us all safe!"

11.m_mPlotText: "Right now, the most important thing is to get my message to him before my Awakened state ends."

12.m_mPlotText: "I've written everything I want to say on the back of this letter. The rest is up to you, Noah!"

13.m_mPlotText: "As the last reinforcing Church knight fell, Hati's battle was also drawing to a close."

14.m_mPlotText: "(It's risky, but there won't be any other Church Knights to interfere for now. Time to find this Moonblessed...)"

15.m_mPlotText: "(Hati's Awakened state won't last long. We don't have much time to talk.)"

16.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Hati has decided to risk herself to draw out the mysterious defender. I must hurry to see what happens."
"Unexpectedly, Ami has sent me a letter after such a long silence."

2.m_mPlotText: "Noah, I think I've been experiencing hallucinations lately... or perhaps, auditory ones?"

3.m_mPlotText: "It's strange, and yet... somehow it feels perfectly normal here."

4.m_mPlotText: "How can you be sure they're hallucinations?"

5.m_mPlotText: "I think I heard someone calling me from within the conch shell."

6.m_mPlotText: "Is it that conch shell you always use to listen to the ocean waves?"

7.m_mPlotText: "Usually I listen to the ocean waves before bed, but a few nights ago, I suddenly heard a call."

8.m_mPlotText: "It looks like an ordinary conch shell..."

9.m_mPlotText: "Recently, whenever I bring the shell close, I can hear that voice."

10.m_mPlotText: "It's a voice that's hard to describe—not any language from this continent, but more like a call resonating through my bloodline."

11.m_mPlotText: "And it seems to be constantly calling me back to Landis..."

12.m_mPlotText: "Could it be the Calamity's deception?"

13.m_mPlotText: "It might really be just your imagination."

14.m_mPlotText: "When I hear that voice, I feel my sanity slipping away... it's hard to tell what's real anymore..."

15.m_mPlotText: "I... I don't know..."

16.m_mPlotText: "Anyway, I've asked Feuler to bring you the conch shell. Give it a listen yourself."

17.m_mPlotText: "Listen and tell me if those voices are really just in my head."

18.m_mPlotText: "Fine."

19.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I have some good news."

2.m_mPlotText: "What a coincidence, I have bad news."

3.m_mPlotText: "Why don't you go first?"

4.m_mPlotText: "The bad news is, I can only hear ocean waves from the conch shell, nothing else."

5.m_mPlotText: "Now for my good news: the voice I heard from the conch shell was somewhat similar to Calamity's, but after giving you the shell, I haven't heard it again. So it probably wasn't Calamity's call—after all, Calamity is everywhere."

6.m_mPlotText: "In that case, the matter is resolved."

7.m_mPlotText: "Aren't you curious?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Not curious."

9.m_mPlotText: "I am curious."

10.m_mPlotText: "These long adventures have taught me one thing: one shouldn't be too curious."

11.m_mPlotText: "Though I am curious, there are many unsolved mysteries, and not every one of them needs to be investigated."

12.m_mPlotText: "But I still want to know what that sound was. Otherwise, this matter will keep haunting me like a shadow I can't shake off."

13.m_mPlotText: "Is there anything you need me to do?"

14.m_mPlotText: "Not at the moment. I already have something in mind. I'll let you know once there's progress."

15.m_mPlotText: "By the way, you can return the conch shell to me now."

16.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Ami has been spending an unusual amount of time in the library lately. I should ask her what's going on."

2.m_mPlotText: "Didn't you say you had a plan? Everyone in the castle says you've been spending all your time in the library lately."

3.m_mPlotText: "You're not eating the library books, are you?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Ready to hit the books?"

5.m_mPlotText: "The ink tastes terrible, not good at all."

6.m_mPlotText: "You actually ate some?!"

7.m_mPlotText: "I have no interest in human knowledge."

8.m_mPlotText: "Are either of us even human?"

9.m_mPlotText: "I want to find books with records of the Landis family."

10.m_mPlotText: "But I haven't found much detail. Only fragments appear in books from when the Landis family was at their height of power."

11.m_mPlotText: "For example, in "The Legend of the Iron Knight," it says: "When the Iron Knight's travels brought him to the Landis family, they were celebrating a sea festival. The Iron Knight received such generous hospitality, with endless wine and delicacies, that his adventuring spirit was corrupted...""

12.m_mPlotText: "It seems they were once a prosperous family, but now everything has sunk into obscurity."

13.m_mPlotText: "Is there any other way to learn more about the Landis family's history..."

14.m_mPlotText: "Actually, I..."

16.m_mPlotText: "No further replies came—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Noah, could you help me with something?"

2.m_mPlotText: "I was about to come looking for you myself."

3.m_mPlotText: "A lot of fish have been mysteriously disappearing from the kitchen lately. You wouldn't happen to know anything about that, would you?"

4.m_mPlotText: "I've been using those fish for some experiments."

5.m_mPlotText: "How are the experiments going?"

6.m_mPlotText: "Pretty good, but I'll need you to catch one more fish before I can call it a complete success."

7.m_mPlotText: "Catch another fish?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Noah, catch me a big fish from the depths where Landis sank."

10.m_mPlotText: "Okay."

11.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

12.m_mPlotText: "Returning to the sunken depths with a different mindset brought new experiences. I caught a massive fish for Ami—one that looks like it could outlive both of us combined."

1.m_mPlotText: "I caught the big fish Ami wanted, but I hope she's not going to eat it whole again..."
"(In the depths of night, I returned to my room. The furnishings, though familiar, held subtle differences from memory—enough to stir disquiet in my heart.)"

2.m_mPlotText: "(An old candlestick—one I had discarded—now stood once more upon my desk.)"

3.m_mPlotText: "(Beneath the wavering candlelight, a letter lay waiting.)"

4.m_mPlotText: "(The envelope bore a dignified, timeworn elegance—its design once common in ages past.)"

5.m_mPlotText: "(The handwriting was Aiona's, though the page was marked by ink blots and corrections. Perhaps, in that moment, her heart was as restless as mine.)"

6.m_mPlotText: "Noticed that?"

7.m_mPlotText: "Noticed what?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Your room... something has changed."

9.m_mPlotText: "So it wasn't just my imagination."

10.m_mPlotText: "The new candlestick is gone—and the one I discarded is back on my desk."

11.m_mPlotText: "It was different. I returned it to its original place."

12.m_mPlotText: "...I thought the timeline collapsed again."

13.m_mPlotText: "...What?"

14.m_mPlotText: "Only this way can the timeline remain stable."

15.m_mPlotText: "Otherwise, the timeline will collapse."

16.m_mPlotText: "But life always shifts in little ways. Nothing stays exactly the same."

17.m_mPlotText: "If they accumulate, the consequences will be severe."

18.m_mPlotText: "We must be careful."

19.m_mPlotText: "I cannot fail again..."

20.m_mPlotText: "Easy, Aiona. You've already left that desert behind."

21.m_mPlotText: "Left...?"

22.m_mPlotText: "But all I remember… is the yellow sand."

23.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "(At dusk, I returned to my room. The furnishings, though familiar, held subtle differences from memory—enough to stir disquiet in my heart.)"

2.m_mPlotText: "(Two candlesticks sat upon the desk—one old, one new.)"

3.m_mPlotText: "(Beneath the twin flames, a letter awaited.)"

4.m_mPlotText: "(Compared to the last, the mistakes had lessened. But the handwriting still trembled.)"

5.m_mPlotText: "Sorry."

6.m_mPlotText: "I found the candlestick and brought it back. It's on the desk now."

7.m_mPlotText: "You were right. I need to learn to accept things as they are."

8.m_mPlotText: "It's fine."

9.m_mPlotText: "My room doesn't need to be so bright anyway."

10.m_mPlotText: "Thank you for the hourglass, Noah."

11.m_mPlotText: "I noticed—without turning it over, time no longer flows in reverse."

12.m_mPlotText: "You're welcome."

13.m_mPlotText: "Have you remembered anything more?"

14.m_mPlotText: "In the desert… there were figures made of yellow sand. Many of them."

15.m_mPlotText: "(Her handwriting trembled even more.)"

16.m_mPlotText: "They stood in silence, each in a different pose."

17.m_mPlotText: "But none of them had faces."

18.m_mPlotText: "Time had worn everything away."

19.m_mPlotText: "And yet—I still remember who they were."

20.m_mPlotText: "Friedrich. Gilrain. Empousa. Hati. Ami..."

21.m_mPlotText: "I reached out to them. I tried to save them all."

22.m_mPlotText: "But in the end… I failed every one of them."

23.m_mPlotText: "It wasn't your fault."

24.m_mPlotText: "It's all behind us now."

25.m_mPlotText: "I saw you too."

26.m_mPlotText: "Countless Noahs… standing silent across the sands."

27.m_mPlotText: "I wanted to reach out."

28.m_mPlotText: "But the moment I touched you, you crumbled into sand."

1.m_mPlotText: "(At dawn, I returned to my room.)"

2.m_mPlotText: "(A single dewy Wolfsbane rested on the desk.)"

3.m_mPlotText: "(Beside it lay a letter.)"

4.m_mPlotText: "(The parchment was pristine, the handwriting neat and composed.)"

5.m_mPlotText: "Noah, this flower is for you."

6.m_mPlotText: "Last night, Hati and Empousa invited me to the greenhouse to tend the Wolfsbane together."

7.m_mPlotText: "To see Wolfsbane again brought me comfort."

8.m_mPlotText: "I wanted to share that feeling with you."

9.m_mPlotText: "I'm glad you're beginning to embrace new changes."

10.m_mPlotText: "I saw the relic you left behind."

11.m_mPlotText: "When was the last time I touched it with my own hands…?"

12.m_mPlotText: "I can no longer remember."

13.m_mPlotText: "I'm sorry."

14.m_mPlotText: "Did the relic feel like a burden to you?"

15.m_mPlotText: "I'm not blaming you."

16.m_mPlotText: "Noah… have you heard of the Alita family's rite?"

17.m_mPlotText: "Only in passing."

18.m_mPlotText: "They remove the bearer's eyes and replace them with the ones passed down through the generations. All to fulfill the family's mission."

19.m_mPlotText: "To most, it's a cruel ritual."

20.m_mPlotText: "But for the Alita heir, it is fate."

21.m_mPlotText: "One of me… One of the many Aionas once resisted that duty. She refused to become a puppet of her bloodline."

22.m_mPlotText: "She didn't want to be reduced to a vessel for another's eyes."

23.m_mPlotText: "Everyone has the right to choose how they live."

24.m_mPlotText: "Everyone must take responsibility for their choice."

25.m_mPlotText: "But we also bear the consequences of those choices."

26.m_mPlotText: "Still… I pity her, for never having the freedom to choose at all."

27.m_mPlotText: "This kind of dilemma haunts every Aiona."

28.m_mPlotText: "Even if we walk forward with conviction, we still find ourselves wondering about the road we left behind."

29.m_mPlotText: "Even the Aiona writing to me now?"

1.m_mPlotText: "(After hearing Aiona's wish to return home, I began discussing the journey's details with her.)"

2.m_mPlotText: "When do we depart?"

3.m_mPlotText: "In three days."

4.m_mPlotText: "You probably already know this, but I feel I should say it anyway."

5.m_mPlotText: "Aiona… the Alitas have been gone for a long time."

6.m_mPlotText: "I know."

7.m_mPlotText: "Thank you for your concern."

8.m_mPlotText: "But that's exactly why I must go. To see what became of my homeland."

9.m_mPlotText: "And to understand what I'm meant to become, now that they’re gone."

10.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Noah, I'm ready now."
"Late at night, Feuler delivers a letter faintly scented with Wolfsbane."

2.m_mPlotText:
"Though I write this letter, I know it is to remain unanswered.

The century-long feud between the houses of Ganelon and Bathory finally subsided after the blight, yet this once-lush peninsula has been reduced to desolation. I walk amongst the ruins of Mouret and find only emptiness as far as the eye sees, save for those fields of Wolfsbane, growing ever wild.

They speak of the house of Bathory's decline in the shadow of Holy War. Yet still, though the castle lies just beyond the river, I dare not return to my homeland."

3.m_mPlotText:
"Lost souls of the Hall of the Elders, have ye found solace? Descendants of Michelangelo, doest thine keep watch over the young Vassals? In the dungeons below, are the poor miscreants still shackled?

In the darkest hour, may mercy be upon ye.

"

4.m_mPlotText: "(A letter addressed to the castle. The sender seems to be an old acquaintance of the castle? I've heard tales of its former glory. As its new master, a polite reply seems fitting.)"

5.m_mPlotText: "I don't know your connection to Bathory, but this place clearly holds memories for you."

6.m_mPlotText: "The castle stands well. It's quieter now, but under the guidance of the Hall of the Elders, order remains."

7.m_mPlotText: "Who are you...? Why would a letter come from the castle?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Impossible."

9.m_mPlotText: "Every rumor speaks of Bathory's downfall. The castle should have been deserted long ago."

10.m_mPlotText: "Wait... the letter was addressed to the old master's private post."

11.m_mPlotText: "...The Hall of the Elders still endures?"

12.m_mPlotText: "Don't tell me… you're the new master of House Bathory?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Identify yourself before making demands."

14.m_mPlotText: "Seeking intelligence, are we?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Merely an old friend, long wandering in exile. Pay me no mind."

16.m_mPlotText: "Forgive me. I meant no offense."

17.m_mPlotText: "It's just... I never expected a reply."

18.m_mPlotText: "Since the Holy War ended, no reports have surfaced of Bloodborn hunting humans in The Howling Peninsula."

19.m_mPlotText: "Which means the Church must have eradicated the Bloodborn entirely."

20.m_mPlotText: "If you truly are an old friend of House Bathory, then you must be Bloodborn yourself."

21.m_mPlotText: "Yet here you are, alive and well, still writing to me."

22.m_mPlotText: "Unless… you're not who you claim to be."

23.m_mPlotText: "Maybe you're working with someone else. Someone watching the Bathory from the shadows. The Church, perhaps."

24.m_mPlotText: "You wrote to gather intel."

25.m_mPlotText: "If the castle's layout remains unchanged, the four Elder chairs in the Hall of the Elders should still encircle the great hall, with the head of house seat at the center. Am I correct?"

26.m_mPlotText: "I was indeed once bound to the Bathory, yet unlike the others, I am not sustained by human blood."

27.m_mPlotText: "As am I."

28.m_mPlotText: "...You as well?"

29.m_mPlotText: "If you wish to continue this discourse, you must first reveal yourself."

31.m_mPlotText: "If you're truly an old friend of the Bathory, why the secrecy?"

33.m_mPlotText: "(How strange... What dark purpose drives this elusive correspondent Q?)"

1.m_mPlotText: "A familiar envelope catches your eye. You recognize it immediately as correspondence from the enigmatic G."

2.m_mPlotText: "I'm writing again to offer my sincerest apologies."

3.m_mPlotText: "I confess my previous correspondence was imprudent. I disregarded the precarious circumstances facing the Bathory and pressed you with questions better left unasked."

4.m_mPlotText: "You have my word that nothing you share shall pass these lips to another soul."

5.m_mPlotText: "Through the long years, I have maintained a silent vigil over the Bathory lineage from the shadows."

6.m_mPlotText: "The castle harbors too many echoes of my former life, yet circumstances now bar me from ever crossing its threshold again."

7.m_mPlotText: "It brings me comfort to know that the Bathory bloodline now serves under new leadership—someone wise enough to leave old ways behind and lead with a clearer vision."

8.m_mPlotText: "I have one final favor to ask of you. This request is a matter of life and death to me. It may prove equally vital to Noah."

9.m_mPlotText: "If you're willing to listen, please write back."

10.m_mPlotText: "(That suspicious correspondent Q again—the one who claims to be an old friend of the Bathorys...)"

11.m_mPlotText: "(How could she possibly know my name? I never revealed it to her.)"

12.m_mPlotText: "You're mistaken. I'm not Noah."

13.m_mPlotText: "Be honest with me, or you'll get nothing."

14.m_mPlotText: "I'm the one who made you suspicious."

15.m_mPlotText: "...My name is Quinn."

16.m_mPlotText: "Please don't tell anyone in the castle that I've been contacting you."

17.m_mPlotText: "...My name is Quinn."

18.m_mPlotText: "Forgive me for keeping secrets from you before. Please, I beg you—don't let anyone in the castle know I've been writing to you."

19.m_mPlotText: "Since you wrote back, I'll take that as a sign you're willing to hear what I have to ask."

20.m_mPlotText: "There's something I left behind in the castle—something precious beyond measure."

21.m_mPlotText: "But I don't know where I lost it, so I need to return and search for it."

22.m_mPlotText: "You don't want anyone knowing we're in contact, yet you want to return to the castle..."

23.m_mPlotText: "You want me to provide cover for you?"

24.m_mPlotText: "...As head of the household, withdrawing those Blood Servants and souls would be a simple matter."

25.m_mPlotText: "Knowing your name changes nothing. I have no reason to risk myself for some mysterious "old friend.""

26.m_mPlotText: "That relic of mine—it would grant you the freedom to walk beneath the sun."

27.m_mPlotText: "Surely that's what every Bloodborn yearns for above all else?"

28.m_mPlotText: "No need. I have no desire to walk beneath the sun."

31.m_mPlotText: "Walking in shadow is no burden to me."

33.m_mPlotText: "You're quite different from the other Bloodborn I've encountered."

34.m_mPlotText: "Don't you ever long for the warmth of daylight?"

35.m_mPlotText: "It's all right... you know where to find me."

36.m_mPlotText: "If you change your mind, you can reach out to me anytime."

37.m_mPlotText: "I truly long to return and see it again."

1.m_mPlotText: "Only through the family records did I uncover the truth—Quinn was a criminal who had brought harm to our clan."

2.m_mPlotText: "She represents a threat to all who dwell within these walls and cannot be permitted to move freely."

3.m_mPlotText: "Why not use her desire to visit the castle and lure her into the open?"

4.m_mPlotText: "I've given considerable thought to your request to visit."

5.m_mPlotText: "Since the castle still holds meaning for you, you're welcome to visit. I see no harm in it."

6.m_mPlotText: "Noah, I'm delighted to receive your letter."

7.m_mPlotText: "I give you my word—I seek only to retrieve something I left behind. Once found, I'll depart at once and trouble no one."

8.m_mPlotText: "In return, I'll share with you the secret of walking in sunlight."

9.m_mPlotText: "That won't be necessary."

10.m_mPlotText: "You might not care, but perhaps your Moonblessed friend would be interested?"

11.m_mPlotText: "Are you investigating me again?"

12.m_mPlotText: "I've been hearing things about you from a friend these past few days."

13.m_mPlotText: "You call yourselves Moonblessed, don't you?"

14.m_mPlotText: "That's hardly news."

15.m_mPlotText: "I've truly fallen behind the times."

16.m_mPlotText: "My understanding remains rooted in an era when the Bloodborn sought to transform the entire continent into their feeding ground."

17.m_mPlotText: "Learning that such a gentle faction as the Moonblessed has emerged among the Bloodborn brings me such pleasant surprise."

18.m_mPlotText: "You yearn to break free from the shackles of flesh and journey to the other side where souls dwell... Such an ideal is both romantic and admirable."

19.m_mPlotText: "Then what are you suggesting?"

20.m_mPlotText: "In your ideals, I glimpse echoes of who I once was."

21.m_mPlotText: "...The self that refused to surrender hope."

22.m_mPlotText: "That's merely your imagination. The Moonblessed are nothing more than wanderers seeking a place to belong."

23.m_mPlotText: "But then again... aren't all who harbor ideals strangers in their own right?"

24.m_mPlotText: "I've written a song for you. I'll share it when we meet."

25.m_mPlotText: "Who are you, truly? The closer I draw to you, the more you slip beyond my grasp."

26.m_mPlotText: "When we stand face to face, all will be laid bare—my past, my heart, every secret I've harbored..."

27.m_mPlotText: "Tomorrow when midnight strikes, by the castle's side gate. I'll be waiting in the shadows."

28.m_mPlotText: "Remember our pact: come alone. Trust no one else with this moment."

1.m_mPlotText: "Quinn had slipped into the castle while I slept, her presence as silent as shadow."

2.m_mPlotText: "The delicate verse she left behind was the only trace of her nocturnal visit."

3.m_mPlotText: "And yet, the castle remained untouched. The calamity I feared never came."

4.m_mPlotText: "What drives this enigmatic girl? What desires lie behind her cryptic actions?"

5.m_mPlotText: "You arrived well past midnight. Our meeting was long overdue."

6.m_mPlotText: "I retrieved that old relic while you slept. There's no need for you to carry that burden anymore."

7.m_mPlotText: "Forgive my tardiness, and my silence upon arrival."

8.m_mPlotText: "But... you hardly honored your promise to come alone that night, did you?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Enough pretense. I know who you really are."

10.m_mPlotText: "False words beget false hearts."

11.m_mPlotText: "...You know, don't you?"

12.m_mPlotText: "I had hoped you would be different from the others."

13.m_mPlotText: "So you stand with Father as well."

14.m_mPlotText: "...You know, don't you?"

15.m_mPlotText: "I see. Father has spoken to you."

16.m_mPlotText: "I thought you'd be different from them."

17.m_mPlotText: "What father? Is this just another lie to throw me off the scent?"

18.m_mPlotText: "I found your records in the family records. Quinn Baphomet—marked as a fugitive who harmed the clan."

19.m_mPlotText: "So that's what the records say..."

20.m_mPlotText: "Now that I've retrieved the old relic, I suppose I can be honest with you."

21.m_mPlotText: "I am indeed a family fugitive. Elder Baphomet... he is my father."

22.m_mPlotText: "Ever since I escaped from the castle years ago, he has been sending hunters after me."

23.m_mPlotText: "That's why I long to return to the castle, yet have never dared set foot there again."

24.m_mPlotText: "Because the moment I return, I will surely be thrown back into the dungeon."

25.m_mPlotText: "You may not believe me, but if any of the old servants still live in the castle, you can ask them for the truth."

26.m_mPlotText: "I'll look into everything you've told me."

27.m_mPlotText: "But if that's what kept you from returning to the castle, you can rest easy now."

28.m_mPlotText: "Rest easy? What do you mean...?"

31.m_mPlotText: "So your hostility toward me... it wasn't born from father's shadow after all."

32.m_mPlotText: "How much has shifted within these walls during my years of exile..."

33.m_mPlotText: "Now that the misunderstandings have been laid to rest, Noah... might we finally meet?"

34.m_mPlotText: "I will share with you the secret of how to "walk in the sunlight.""

35.m_mPlotText: "This time... can we both honor our promises?"

37.m_mPlotText: "(After our exchange, I sought out Cain immediately, determined to scrutinize every claim Quinn had made.)"

38.m_mPlotText: "(His account vindicated her completely—three centuries past, Elder Baphomet's sole daughter had indeed vanished from these halls under circumstances that remain shrouded in mystery.)"

39.m_mPlotText: "(Yet if she had already reclaimed what she sought and fulfilled her purpose, what compelled her to risk this dangerous meeting?)"

1.m_mPlotText: "Quinn's enigmatic secrets are beginning to unravel, yet the shadows of past misunderstandings and suspicions have woven a delicate web of apprehension around this fated meeting."
"Feuler's wings flutter as he delivers a letter bearing a wax seal."

2.m_mPlotText:
"Esteemed Lord Bathory,

This month marks the Kingdom's routine survey, conducted once every fifty years.
We shall dispatch our finest cartographer to your territory for comprehensive surveying. The scope encompasses: the Bathory family's main city, subsidiary settlements, and adjacent townships. Given the thoroughness of this deep survey, considerable time will be required. Please inform the residents in advance and prepare for the necessary cooperation.

Agnes, the Greatest Cartographer on the Continent"

3.m_mPlotText: "(A wax-sealed letter and talk of an official survey? This has all the hallmarks of an elaborate new scam. Best to ignore it entirely.)"

4.m_mPlotText: "In the days that followed, a series of letters arrived in rapid succession, each bearing increasingly stern and insistent language."

5.m_mPlotText: "If there is no reply after the first letter is sent, issue the following reminder."

6.m_mPlotText: "Please take note!"

7.m_mPlotText: "Collaborating with the cartographer's surveys stands as a sacred duty for all citizens of Minexus."

8.m_mPlotText: "This survey bears profound significance—it enriches our cultural legacy, safeguards this era's treasures, and ensures the transmission of wisdom to generations unborn."

9.m_mPlotText: "(Keep ignoring.)"

11.m_mPlotText: "If no reply after the second letter, send the following reminder."

12.m_mPlotText: "Please take note!"

13.m_mPlotText: "I reiterate: cooperation with our survey is the sacred obligation of every citizen of Minexus."

14.m_mPlotText: "These survey requests are made purely as a courtesy—and to guarantee the smooth execution of our essential work."

15.m_mPlotText: "All resistance to our survey efforts is utterly futile."

16.m_mPlotText: "Whether you respond or not is irrelevant—we will conduct our survey at the scheduled time and location as planned."

17.m_mPlotText: "(Have scam organizations really become this aggressive just to get a response these days?)"

18.m_mPlotText: "(Or perhaps I've misjudged the situation. The cartographers could be a legitimate organization simply following established protocols.)"

19.m_mPlotText: "(No matter who they really are, I can't let them come here.)"

20.m_mPlotText: "(Otherwise, the secret that the family has become Bloodborn will inevitably be exposed.)"

21.m_mPlotText: "If no response is received after the third letter, proceed to send the following notice in accordance with the survey protocol."

22.m_mPlotText: "Please take note!"

23.m_mPlotText: "The initial survey of Bathory territory shall commence at dusk, three days hence."

24.m_mPlotText: "The first survey location will be—"

25.m_mPlotText: "(For the sake of the Vassals within the castle, I must respond after all.)"

26.m_mPlotText: "Hello."

27.m_mPlotText: "It appears you sent materials that aren't required to be included in the protocol."

28.m_mPlotText: "Huh?"

29.m_mPlotText: "Since I haven't received any reply, I thought the castle was abandoned."

30.m_mPlotText: "Sorry for the delay in replying—there have been many affairs in the territory lately."

31.m_mPlotText: "I have some questions about this survey."

34.m_mPlotText: "Whether you reply or not, I'll be there on time. Regulations are regulations."

35.m_mPlotText: "Alright, enough small talk. I have work to do."

36.m_mPlotText: "The initial survey of Bathory territory shall commence at dusk, three days hence."

37.m_mPlotText: "The first survey location will be the back garden of Bathory Castle."

39.m_mPlotText: "We will dispatch a professional cartographer to conduct detailed on-site surveying and documentation."

40.m_mPlotText: "Could we have more time? Three days feels too rushed—I need to consult with the castle residents and make proper arrangements."

41.m_mPlotText: "The surveying will cover terrain features, principal building structures, botanical distribution patterns, and..."

42.m_mPlotText: "Might it be possible to extend the timeline by a few days?"

43.m_mPlotText: "The surveying personnel will carry standard cartographic instruments, including..."

44.m_mPlotText: "Miss Agnes? Are you receiving my messages?"

45.m_mPlotText: "Throughout the surveying process, please ensure the designated survey area remains unobstructed..."

47.m_mPlotText: "At long last, Agnes brought her notification to a close."

48.m_mPlotText: "The above notification takes effect immediately. That is all."

49.m_mPlotText: "Ugh, this survey notification manual Grandfather gave me is exactly like him—endlessly verbose and mind-numbingly tedious."

50.m_mPlotText: "Thank goodness I've finished transcribing it all."

1.m_mPlotText: "To safeguard Bathory's secrets, I must prevent Agnes from conducting her survey."

2.m_mPlotText: "It's a good idea for me to carry out the survey instead—this way, she will also save time and effort."

3.m_mPlotText: "Would you allow me to handle the territory survey for you?"

4.m_mPlotText: "All that surveying must be exhausting. Perhaps you'd like to take a moment's rest?"

5.m_mPlotText: "Absolutely not. I endured countless hardships to evade Grandfather's watchful eyes and reach this era."

6.m_mPlotText: "I refuse to leave a single corner of this place uninspected!"

7.m_mPlotText: "Absolutely not. I endured countless hardships to evade Grandfather's watchful eyes and reach this era."

8.m_mPlotText: "How could you possibly suggest taking a vacation right now!"

9.m_mPlotText: "Every single day here is fresh and joyful to me!"

10.m_mPlotText: "Most people I know spend their days looking for ways to avoid work."

11.m_mPlotText: "I've never met anyone quite so passionate about their work."

12.m_mPlotText: "But work needs to be done in moderation too. Why not leave the surveying to Bathory's Lord? That would be the safe approach."

13.m_mPlotText: "Wait, I didn't notice before—is this letter from Bathory?"

14.m_mPlotText: "Oh, suddenly my legs are feeling a bit sore."

15.m_mPlotText: "You're absolutely right! Work should be done in moderation—why not take that break after all!"

16.m_mPlotText: "Then the surveying is entrusted to you. It's decided, my Lord."

17.m_mPlotText: "Why did you change your mind upon realizing it was a letter from the Bathory family?"

18.m_mPlotText: "Did you have an unpleasant experience during the last survey?"

19.m_mPlotText: "Let me be clear—I'm not running away from this."

20.m_mPlotText: "Every cartographer has their weak spots!"

21.m_mPlotText: "I saw those things in the castle..."

22.m_mPlotText: "Those things may terrify me... but that doesn't diminish the fact that I am the continent's greatest cartographer!"

23.m_mPlotText: "Alright then, I'll have the cartographic instruments sent to you presently."

24.m_mPlotText: "Surveying work is no simple matter. Should you fail to meet the requirements, I will personally see to it at the castle..."

25.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

26.m_mPlotText: "(Just what are these things that have Agnes so thoroughly spooked...)"

27.m_mPlotText: "(Did her surveying work inadvertently lead her to our secret?)"

28.m_mPlotText: "(Since she's clearly avoiding the topic, it suggests she won't be a threat in the near future.)"

29.m_mPlotText: "(Then I'll proceed as planned—complete the survey task in her stead.)"

1.m_mPlotText: "After completing the survey, I had Feuler deliver the survey maps to Agnes."

2.m_mPlotText: "But just as Feuler departed, Swaney arrived with Agnes's letter to the study."

3.m_mPlotText: "Did you receive those three packages?"

4.m_mPlotText: "There were... some complications."

5.m_mPlotText: "Really appreciate the packages. The survey nearly failed without them."

6.m_mPlotText: "You finally realized you sent the wrong things?"

7.m_mPlotText: "I stayed up too late reading the night before I sent those packages... I was still half-asleep when I packaged everything, so I accidentally mixed them up."

8.m_mPlotText: "Those storybooks—I had to plead with the bookstore owner for ages before he finally agreed to lend them to me! Please, I'm counting on you to take good care of them."

9.m_mPlotText: "Thankfully, the survey work wasn't affected."

10.m_mPlotText: "Wait—survey?"

11.m_mPlotText: "You actually started surveying without any instruments?"

12.m_mPlotText: "I had the survey maps sent to you with urgency."

13.m_mPlotText: "So that should wrap up the survey task, right?"

14.m_mPlotText: "What?!"

15.m_mPlotText: "You're already done with the survey?! It's only been two days!"

16.m_mPlotText: "This is your first survey, and you didn't even have proper instruments—how could you finish so fast?"

17.m_mPlotText: "I hope you'll forgive any mistakes I might have made."

18.m_mPlotText: "Wait for me!"

19.m_mPlotText: "Time drifted by..."

20.m_mPlotText: "The survey maps from the castle—they've finally arrived!"

21.m_mPlotText: "Though the linework still bears traces of inexperience, the precision of detail and the masterful capture of atmosphere stand out..."

22.m_mPlotText: "To create such artistry in so perilous a place..."

23.m_mPlotText: "Noah, you wouldn't happen to be some sort of secret cartographic prodigy, would you?"

24.m_mPlotText: "Thanks..."

25.m_mPlotText: "So, does that mean I can call it quits on the survey?"

26.m_mPlotText: "Wait."

27.m_mPlotText: "I've got an ominous feeling."

28.m_mPlotText: "I've decided..."

30.m_mPlotText: "You're a talent that can't be missed."

31.m_mPlotText: "Missing out is the norm in life."

32.m_mPlotText: "North of the castle lies a town called Elfriede."

33.m_mPlotText: "We're not finished here yet, Lord. Keep moving!"

37.m_mPlotText: "Don't you dare try that 'read but don't reply' trick on me—I know exactly where your castle is."

38.m_mPlotText: "Even though I'm terrified of those things in the castle... if you won't agree, I'll find the courage to survey it myself!"

40.m_mPlotText: "How dedicated of you. I knew I could count on you."

43.m_mPlotText: "You know, you really do have excellent taste in books."

44.m_mPlotText: "Consider the next survey my payment for borrowing your book."

1.m_mPlotText: "The survey wasn't completed within the agreed timeframe."

2.m_mPlotText: "Though I'd rather she didn't come in person, she deserves to know the truth."

3.m_mPlotText: "I'm sorry—I wasn't able to complete the survey on time."

4.m_mPlotText: "I encountered some contingencies in the village that demanded immediate attention."

5.m_mPlotText: "If there's no rush, I could always make another trip in the coming days."

6.m_mPlotText: "That won't be necessary."

7.m_mPlotText: "That's... not the reaction I was expecting."

8.m_mPlotText: "I thought you'd storm the castle and never let me off."

9.m_mPlotText: "I was bracing myself for you to burst through the gates and confront me."

10.m_mPlotText: "I wasn't expecting such a... measured approach."

11.m_mPlotText: "Precisely. This is indeed a time-limited trial."

12.m_mPlotText: "But not the trial you imagined. It's human nature being tested."

13.m_mPlotText: "Surprising, yet not so surprising."

14.m_mPlotText: "Was this all a setup?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Between your survey task and moral duty, you made a choice that truly pleased me!"

16.m_mPlotText: "You chose to help the troubled people."

17.m_mPlotText: "Yet you also took care to consider those poor pet bats."

18.m_mPlotText: "If I'm not mistaken, that carriage you sent back to the castle was loaded with food for them, wasn't it?"

19.m_mPlotText: "Balancing both sides' needs is never easy, yet you embraced this difficult path without a moment's hesitation."

20.m_mPlotText: "In the end, you withstood the pressure and honestly reported the survey's failure to me."

21.m_mPlotText: "Your performance was truly exceptional!"

22.m_mPlotText: "Merely a Lord's duty."

23.m_mPlotText: "But... you owe me an explanation."

24.m_mPlotText: "You know far too much about my affairs."

25.m_mPlotText: "Tell me honestly—when did you start watching me?"

26.m_mPlotText: "You've been following me all this time—what else have you witnessed?"

27.m_mPlotText: "I want to know everything—tell me what you know about the Bathory."

28.m_mPlotText: "You can trust me—protecting everyone's secrets is a cartographer's sacred duty."

31.m_mPlotText: "Tomorrow night, at this very hour—come to Starfall Valley, alone."

34.m_mPlotText: "(She's actually gone quiet... no more messages from her...)"

35.m_mPlotText: "(Her position, and how much she knows about the family's secret—both directly affect the family's safety. What should I do?)"

36.m_mPlotText: "As I lay contemplating the mysteries that tomorrow night might unveil, sleep began to claim me..."

37.m_mPlotText: "Sharp knocking shattered my slumber. Someone had delivered a letter."

38.m_mPlotText: "Oh! The storybooks—you mustn't forget to bring them!"

40.m_mPlotText: "(What kind of villain reminds their opponent to bring the borrowed books before a duel?)"

1.m_mPlotText: "Agnes chose Starfall Valley as our meeting place. Something about this feels... wrong."
"I discovered a secret—when I place the Siren's Tear beside my pillow, she appears in my dreams."

2.m_mPlotText: "The dream unfolded in a lavish mansion. Was this her office? No... I remembered the furniture was different."

3.m_mPlotText: "The thick scent of blood hung in the air. Blood always followed her—was that why they called her the Mistbound Terror?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Help me clean up this mess, little one."

5.m_mPlotText: "She tapped my shoulder from behind with her siren tentacle—this time, we truly touched."

6.m_mPlotText: "I turned to find a corpse by the desk—a well-dressed body, its face frozen in a gruesome expression."

7.m_mPlotText: "How may I help you?"

8.m_mPlotText: "Then—please help me leave a Bloodborn's mark on the corpse."

9.m_mPlotText: "Of course."

10.m_mPlotText: "Too engorged for my taste—I can't manage a bite."

11.m_mPlotText: "Well done, little one."

12.m_mPlotText: "Picky, little one."

13.m_mPlotText: "Who was the victim?"

14.m_mPlotText: "A fool who got in the Association's way."

15.m_mPlotText: "And these documents you're destroying?"

16.m_mPlotText: "Want to see?"

17.m_mPlotText: "She handed me the letter."

18.m_mPlotText: "The letter detailed how the deceased had brazenly boasted about the slaves he purchased from Sapphire Isle—their endurance under torture, and the custom instruments of torment he had commissioned for them."

19.m_mPlotText: "The letter also detailed his plans to breed sirens, aiming to challenge the Association's grip on the slaves."

20.m_mPlotText: "Lorelei burned the first half of the letter and kept the second half."

21.m_mPlotText: "The Sages will approve of the victim I've chosen."

22.m_mPlotText: "Are you using the Mistbound Terror as a disguise to hunt those who abuse sirens?"

23.m_mPlotText: "Just the last shred of goodness in an evil heart."

24.m_mPlotText: "Why not leave this place?"

25.m_mPlotText: "Why not kill the other Sages?"

26.m_mPlotText: "By staying here, I can at least use my position as a Sage to protect a few."

27.m_mPlotText: "Besides... sooner or later, I will lead all my kin back to the sea."

28.m_mPlotText: "Staying with the Sage Association is how I repay the Mysterious Merchant."

29.m_mPlotText: "Besides... the ones truly hunting the sirens are the Masters hiding behind the Sages."

30.m_mPlotText: "(I see her sinking into the mire, yet no path reveals itself to pull her free.)"

31.m_mPlotText: "There must be a way. There must still be a way..."

33.m_mPlotText: "(The moon had risen. The dream was over.)"

1.m_mPlotText: "I refuse to accept that Lorelei is gone forever. If we offer more blood to the Siren's Tear, perhaps..."
"As summer draws to a close, I bid farewell to Sapphire Isle. Before boarding the carriage, Bella and I made a promise to stay in touch."
"Dear Mr. Nevernight, I hope this letter finds you well."

2.m_mPlotText: "I received your gift. The sailors from The Telkhines delivered your package—what is this powder inside?"

3.m_mPlotText: "I'm writing this letter to you from a waystation, where the ice and snow never melt. I wish I could bring you here to witness this magnificent sight."

4.m_mPlotText: "I visited a reclusive alchemist. He told me that saltpeter powder can let you see ice and snow even in Sapphire Isle."

5.m_mPlotText: "Just mix the powder with water, and you'll see 'ice.'"

6.m_mPlotText: "It works!"

7.m_mPlotText: "So, this transparent and freezing substance is 'ice.'"

8.m_mPlotText: "When scraped with a knife, the ice turns into powder that looks just like 'snow.'"

9.m_mPlotText: "'Snow.' It's beautiful, though it disappears so quickly."

10.m_mPlotText: "The snow here never disappears."

11.m_mPlotText: "It hasn't disappeared—it's merely waiting for the next winter's chill."

12.m_mPlotText: "Once you've recovered, let's make this our second destination on our journey together."

13.m_mPlotText: "When it drifts to where it belongs, it will become snow once again."

14.m_mPlotText: "...Thank you, Noah."

15.m_mPlotText: "This is the 'most unique sight' I've ever seen."

16.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "Greetings, Noah. It's been a while since I received your letter. What have you been keeping yourself busy with?"

2.m_mPlotText: "I am searching for the way back to my homeland."

3.m_mPlotText: "Where... is your homeland?"

4.m_mPlotText: "I remember very little."

5.m_mPlotText: "A place that seems connected to the sunset."

6.m_mPlotText: "A place that might be called Earth."

7.m_mPlotText: "Though only fragments remain... I can sense the longing hidden within them."

8.m_mPlotText: "Is that so..."

9.m_mPlotText: "Maybe it's only the homeland left behind on a distant journey that stirs such longing."

10.m_mPlotText: "You don't seem to like Sapphire Isle very much."

11.m_mPlotText: "Sapphire Isle... was such a dull place back then."

12.m_mPlotText: "I wanted to sail with the sailors, but Father said the sea was full of dangers."

13.m_mPlotText: "I wanted to learn the harp, but Uncle said I should rest more."

14.m_mPlotText: "I wanted to discuss music and learn about fascinating new knowledge from books, but Father said I should just learn to be a proper lady and marry a noble who could take good care of me."

15.m_mPlotText: "They cannot understand your pursuits."

16.m_mPlotText: "However, in 'the dullest place—Sapphire Isle,' I met you, Noah, and Lorelei."

17.m_mPlotText: "So... this place isn't so bad after all."

18.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "After hearing Bella's song, I couldn't wait to write back."

2.m_mPlotText: "Thank you for the sheet music."

3.m_mPlotText: "Through the song, I see visions—feelings of my homeland that I had long forgotten."

4.m_mPlotText: "This song was written just for you—it's unique."

5.m_mPlotText: "You seem obsessed with 'unique.'"

6.m_mPlotText: "I'm afraid of becoming someone dull..."

7.m_mPlotText: "Is it because you're afraid of being forgotten?"

8.m_mPlotText: "How about trying to become a Bloodborn instead of a human?"

9.m_mPlotText: "Not really..."

10.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps it truly is an option worth considering."

11.m_mPlotText: "The people of Sapphire Isle are kind, but they're all so dull."

12.m_mPlotText: "One look at Father's morning expression tells me if he had salted cod with bread for breakfast or secretly drank an extra beer."

13.m_mPlotText: "One look at Uncle Rudolf's expression tells me whether he's pretending everything's fine after arguing with his wife, or genuinely happy about a good catch."

14.m_mPlotText: "Dull people have strings attached to them—even without someone pulling those strings, you can easily see what they'll do and how their future will unfold."

15.m_mPlotText: "But I don't want this world to see through me."

16.m_mPlotText: "I refuse to accept that my life, future, and death are all foreseen by someone who calls themselves god."

17.m_mPlotText: "I too want to win the game against the gods."

18.m_mPlotText: "I want to become the new god."

19.m_mPlotText: "Then we are comrades on the same front, right?"

20.m_mPlotText: "You'll make this world a 'unique' place, won't you?"

21.m_mPlotText: "Definitely. This is our promise."

22.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "The moment my hand brushed the cloak, a strange sensation washed over me—like falling, suspended between waking and dream."

2.m_mPlotText: "Ah, little Noah, you actually put it on!"

3.m_mPlotText: "How precious. So eager..."

4.m_mPlotText: "If anyone's eager, it's the person who sent two letters in a row."

5.m_mPlotText: "Just as I thought—something's definitely off about this mantle."

6.m_mPlotText: "Hmm hmm, I came here specially to play with you."

7.m_mPlotText: "Such a chilly welcome. That's not very polite, little Noah."

8.m_mPlotText: "My, my... little Noah has such sharp instincts."

9.m_mPlotText: "Before you explain how you know I just put the mantle on—"

10.m_mPlotText: "Shouldn't we start with proper introductions?"

11.m_mPlotText: "Introductions? Sure."

12.m_mPlotText: "I've never bothered with formalities before, but for you, little Noah, I'll make an exception."

13.m_mPlotText: "A splitting headache strikes without warning."

14.m_mPlotText: "Si...rene... Your name is Sirene?"

15.m_mPlotText: "Indeed. Though you're welcome to call me Master, if you prefer."

16.m_mPlotText: "Stop forcing your name into people's minds."

17.m_mPlotText: "If you're this upset over a little teasing, you'll never survive what's coming."

18.m_mPlotText: "Thanks for the warning. I'll level up my room's security."

19.m_mPlotText: "Can’t have you sneaking more strange things into my closet."

20.m_mPlotText: "Little Noah does have a sense of humor."

21.m_mPlotText: "Don't worry. Your room will be perfectly safe."

22.m_mPlotText: "I'll keep an eye on you, and I won't let anyone lay a hand on you. After all—"

23.m_mPlotText: "I absolutely hate it when people touch what's mine."

24.m_mPlotText: "That's oddly threatening… and somehow cute."

25.m_mPlotText: "Your eyes must be getting tired from all that watching."

27.m_mPlotText: "No one answers, yet I can't shake the feeling that I'm being watched."

28.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps it's time I uncovered who Sirene truly is."

1.m_mPlotText: "I "saw" memories that don't belong to me."

2.m_mPlotText: "If they're not just illusions..."

3.m_mPlotText: "Then I'd guess you're an _Ancient One_—someone who lived through that legendary battle."

4.m_mPlotText: "Oh my."

5.m_mPlotText: "All I did was share my true name, and you've already taken so many memories without asking."

6.m_mPlotText: "Should I praise your cleverness? Or punish your insolence?"

7.m_mPlotText: "You should give me more information."

8.m_mPlotText: "I might just "accidentally" take a little extra."

9.m_mPlotText: "Heheh. You look so adorable when you're desperate. Should I put a collar on you?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Sorry, but my wardrobe doesn't have room for such niche little trinkets."

11.m_mPlotText: "Besides, isn't it the Church you truly want to bring to heel?"

12.m_mPlotText: "Tch... And you think those filthy Church mutts are worthy of such a prize?"

13.m_mPlotText: "Honestly, just their scent alone makes my skin crawl."

14.m_mPlotText: "Judging by your reaction... the two factions I saw in those memories must be the Bloodborn and the Church."

16.m_mPlotText: "My dear Noah, don't pretend indifference while trying to pry into your master's affairs."

17.m_mPlotText: "I've reviewed the records. There were only two major, full-scale wars between the Bloodborn and the Church."

18.m_mPlotText: "Aside from the First Holy War in ancient times..."

19.m_mPlotText: "You must be Sirene of the Shadow Cloak, a Bathory Elder who fought in the Second Holy War."

20.m_mPlotText: "Oh? So fascinated by me that you went digging through the archives..."

21.m_mPlotText: "Then surely, if a revered Family Elder found herself in a bit of trouble, you would eagerly wag your tail to help?"
