22.m_mPlotText: "While I do consider myself helpful, I'm afraid tail-wagging isn't one of my skills."

23.m_mPlotText: "I wonder what species your past Vassals belonged to."

24.m_mPlotText: "Don't worry. You'll get used to that gesture soon enough."

25.m_mPlotText: "Every species you can think of."

26.m_mPlotText: "Of course, if you'd like to join, I'd gladly dismiss them all."

27.m_mPlotText: "Let's first talk about what kind of "small trouble" would make an ancient Elder write a letter begging for help."

28.m_mPlotText: "Insomnia."

30.m_mPlotText: "Fair enough. If I'd woken after sleeping for centuries, I'd be worse off."

31.m_mPlotText: "But next time, try getting to the point a little sooner."

32.m_mPlotText: "Does it matter? You've stayed and talked with me this long, haven't you, dear Noah?"

35.m_mPlotText: "I know a pharmacy. I'll have them prepare some remedies for your insomnia."

36.m_mPlotText: "And if they don't work, you'll take responsibility, won't you?"

37.m_mPlotText: "Then I suggest filing a complaint with the pharmacy."

1.m_mPlotText: "Dear Noah, are you ready to take responsibility?"

2.m_mPlotText: "Please, spare me the lines ripped straight from a romance drama."

3.m_mPlotText: "Is this about saving the world?"

4.m_mPlotText: "Your insomnia remedies are COMPLETELY useless."

5.m_mPlotText: "So what's your plan to fix this mess?"

6.m_mPlotText: "I'm fairly certain "striking down incompetent doctors" isn't part of my job description."

7.m_mPlotText: "No matter how charming you try to be, it doesn't change the fact that you're neglecting your duties."

8.m_mPlotText: "Sounds like you've already started treating me like your Vassal."

9.m_mPlotText: "Who else would it be?"

10.m_mPlotText: "Is there another Elder in this castle more deserving of your undivided devotion?"

11.m_mPlotText: "(Masterfully leaves her on read.)"

12.m_mPlotText: "Silence and avoidance won't get you out of this."

13.m_mPlotText: "Ah. These tortured souls won't stop wailing. I really need someone who can quiet them for me."

14.m_mPlotText: "Care to give it a try, dear Noah?"

15.m_mPlotText: "That's the first time I've heard murder described so poetically."

16.m_mPlotText: "Don't worry. I'd never let you end up like them."

17.m_mPlotText: "I'd keep you locked in my room, making all the lovely sounds I want to fall asleep to."

18.m_mPlotText: "Perhaps future generations will invent something that meets your requirements."

19.m_mPlotText: "Hmph. Seems that thick skull of yours still doesn't understand what a privilege this is."

20.m_mPlotText: "But don't worry. I'll teach you how to please me... One step at a time. Hand in hand."

21.m_mPlotText: "With my own two hands, of course."

22.m_mPlotText: "No wonder you can't sleep, with all these weird thoughts running through your head."

23.m_mPlotText: "Why don't you put those hands to better use and brew yourself some sleeping medicine?"

24.m_mPlotText: "Hmph, you're as stubborn as ever."

25.m_mPlotText: "But the more you resist, the more I want to play with you... hehehe..."

26.m_mPlotText: "No further replies—for now."

1.m_mPlotText: "I've found the cause of my insomnia."

2.m_mPlotText: "That sudden seriousness... I have a bad feeling about this."

3.m_mPlotText: "Do tell. You've got me losing sleep now, too."

4.m_mPlotText: "Hehehe... Only you, dear Noah, would dare speak to me like that."

5.m_mPlotText: "Let's hear about that insomnia of yours."

6.m_mPlotText: "It's the environment."

7.m_mPlotText: "After sleeping in the crypt for so many years, I seem unable to fall asleep without my coffin now."

8.m_mPlotText: "How annoying... That place is terrible for my skin."

9.m_mPlotText: "So we just need to move your coffin into the bedroom?"

10.m_mPlotText: "It's not that simple."

11.m_mPlotText: "I can only sleep soundly in a coffin, in a dark, damp crypt, completely sealed off from the world."

12.m_mPlotText: "Time to revisit some old haunts."

13.m_mPlotText: "Hah! Absolutely not."

14.m_mPlotText: "I refuse to go back to that place."

15.m_mPlotText: "I found an ancient tomb with a similar environment. I should be able to get a good rest there."

16.m_mPlotText: "Congratulations on your recovery. Good night."

17.m_mPlotText: "Come with me."

18.m_mPlotText: "...I knew it."

19.m_mPlotText: "Oh? Dear Noah, are you learning to read your master's mind now?"

20.m_mPlotText: "If you were willing to lie down there quietly by yourself, you wouldn't be writing me these letters."

21.m_mPlotText: "Hehe... Could it be you're waiting for an invitation?"

22.m_mPlotText: "I do."

23.m_mPlotText: "Oh my, how honest you've become."

24.m_mPlotText: "Because you absolutely won't let me go unless I play along until the very end."

25.m_mPlotText: "Hehehe... Good boy, becoming more and more like a puppy."

26.m_mPlotText: "But not today."

27.m_mPlotText: "Sit there like a good boy, tongue out, and wait for your master's reward."

28.m_mPlotText: "No new letters have arrived, and sleep eludes me."

29.m_mPlotText: "To avoid ending up as just another poor soul trapped in Sirene's mantle, it would be wise to prepare some necessary countermeasures."

1.m_mPlotText: "I've prepared both tomb and coffin. Now hurry back to your master when dawn breaks, little Noah."
